WEBVTT

00:32.053 --> 00:32.953
<i>MISSOURI
EARTH 1980</i>

01:21.228 --> 01:22.939
- Come on!
- Slow down.

01:22.939 --> 01:24.786
What do you say, my River Lily?
Come on!

01:27.348 --> 01:29.511
- Where are you taking me?
- Come on, come on, come on.

01:30.785 --> 01:34.039
- Look. Look.
- Oh, it's beautiful!

01:34.039 --> 01:36.219
I was afraid it wouldn't
take to this soil.

01:36.219 --> 01:37.755
But it rooted quickly.

01:37.755 --> 01:40.380
And soon it'll be everywhere.

01:40.380 --> 01:43.161
All across the universe.

01:44.633 --> 01:46.379
Well I don't know what
you're talking about...

01:46.379 --> 01:48.107
...but I like the
way you say it.

01:48.438 --> 01:50.646
My heart is yours...

01:50.646 --> 01:52.081
Meredith Quill.

01:53.539 --> 01:56.466
I can't believe I fell
in love with a spaceman.

02:25.799 --> 02:28.182
34 YEARS LATER

02:32.577 --> 02:36.656
THE SOVEREIGN
PLANET

02:46.914 --> 02:48.581
Showtime, a-holes!

02:49.860 --> 02:51.981
It's gonna be here any minute.

02:51.981 --> 02:53.360
Which will be its loss.

02:54.430 --> 02:56.045
I thought your thing
was a sword.

02:56.045 --> 02:58.282
We've been hired to stop an
inter-dimensional beast...

02:58.282 --> 03:00.901
...from feeding on those batteries,
and I'm gonna stop it with a sword?

03:00.901 --> 03:02.963
It's just, swords were your thing and
guns were mine

03:02.963 --> 03:06.063
but I guess we're both doing guns now.
I just didn't know that.

03:06.676 --> 03:10.481
Drax, why aren't you wearing
one of Rocket's aero-rigs?

03:10.481 --> 03:13.274
- It hurts.
- Hurts?

03:14.669 --> 03:16.122
I have sensitive nipples.

03:17.505 --> 03:20.060
Ha ha ha! My nipples
hurt! Oh goodness me!

03:20.495 --> 03:22.190
What about him?
What's he doing?

03:22.190 --> 03:24.956
I'm finishing this so we can listen
to tunes while we work.

03:24.956 --> 03:27.018
- How is that a priority?
- Blame Quill.

03:27.018 --> 03:28.648
He's the one who loves music so much.

03:28.648 --> 03:32.137
No, I actually agree with Drax on this.
That's hardly important right now.

03:32.783 --> 03:34.593
Oh, Okay.
Sure, Quill.

03:34.593 --> 03:38.356
No, seriously, I side with Drax.

03:38.773 --> 03:42.288
No, I understand that.
You're being very serious right now.

03:42.933 --> 03:44.702
I can clearly see you winking.

03:45.197 --> 03:47.556
Dammit.
I'm using my left eye?

03:53.004 --> 03:54.435
I am Groot!

03:54.435 --> 03:57.455
They were not looking
at you funny.

04:02.722 --> 04:04.022
That's intense.

04:29.357 --> 04:33.322
GUARDIANS OF THE GALAXY VOL. 2

05:09.637 --> 05:10.937
Groot!

05:27.004 --> 05:29.335
Groot, get out of the way!
You're going to get hurt.

05:29.661 --> 05:30.411
Hide.

06:16.389 --> 06:18.989
No, no!
Spit it out, spit it out, c'mon.

06:21.966 --> 06:23.266
Disgusting!

07:28.671 --> 07:31.684
The beast's hide is too thick
to be pierced from the outside.

07:31.684 --> 07:33.782
I must cut through it from the inside.

07:34.709 --> 07:38.198
No, no, Drax!
Wait a minute!

07:46.604 --> 07:47.904
What is he doing?

07:47.904 --> 07:51.081
He said the skin is too thick to be
pierced from the outside, so he....

07:51.081 --> 07:52.979
- That doesn't make any sense!
- I tried telling him that!

07:52.979 --> 07:55.559
Skin's the same level of thickness
from the inside as from the outside!

07:55.559 --> 07:57.060
I realize that.

07:59.623 --> 08:01.325
There is a cut on its neck.

08:01.325 --> 08:04.065
Rocket, get it to look up.

08:06.274 --> 08:09.012
Hey, giant sea monkey!
I'm here!

08:16.709 --> 08:18.009
Watch it, Quill!

08:59.875 --> 09:02.270
Yes!
I have single handedly

09:02.270 --> 09:04.041
vanquished the beast!

09:06.935 --> 09:08.390
What?

09:17.088 --> 09:20.156
- What are they called again?
- Anulax batteries.

09:20.156 --> 09:22.484
Harbulary batteries.

09:22.484 --> 09:24.980
That's nothing like
what I just said.

09:24.980 --> 09:26.639
But they're worth thousands
of units a piece, which is...

09:26.639 --> 09:28.952
why the Sovereign hired
us to protect them.

09:28.952 --> 09:31.101
Careful what you say around these
folks, they're easily offended

09:31.101 --> 09:33.323
The cost of transgression is death.

09:34.216 --> 09:38.408
We thank you Guardians for putting
your lives on the line.

09:38.408 --> 09:42.197
We could not risk the lives of
our own Sovereign citizens.

09:42.197 --> 09:46.180
Every citizen is born exactly
as designed by the community.

09:46.180 --> 09:49.188
Impeccable, both physically
and mentally.

09:49.188 --> 09:51.378
We control the DNA of our progeny

09:51.378 --> 09:53.677
...germinating them in birthing pods.

09:53.677 --> 09:57.438
I guess I prefer to make people
the old fashioned way.

09:58.089 --> 10:00.930
Well.  Perhaps someday you could
give me a history lesson...

10:00.930 --> 10:04.134
...in the archaic ways
of our ancestors

10:04.134 --> 10:05.933
For academic purposes.

10:05.933 --> 10:09.103
I would be honored. Yes.
In the name of research...

10:09.103 --> 10:11.516
I think that could be...

10:11.516 --> 10:13.797
...pretty uh, repulsive. I'm...

10:13.797 --> 10:16.270
- I'm not into that kind of casual...
- Please...

10:16.270 --> 10:19.705
Your people promised something
in exchange for our services.

10:19.705 --> 10:22.493
Bring it and we shall gladly
be on our way.

10:34.808 --> 10:37.423
Family reunion. Yay!

10:37.423 --> 10:39.615
I understand she
is your sister.

10:39.615 --> 10:43.436
She's worth no more to me than
the bounty due for her on Xandar.

10:43.900 --> 10:47.855
Our soldiers apprehended her
attempting to steal the batteries.

10:48.402 --> 10:50.402
Do with her as you please.

10:53.627 --> 10:55.498
We thank you, High Priestess Ayesha.

10:55.498 --> 10:57.870
What is your heritage, Mr. Quill?

11:00.908 --> 11:04.280
- My mother was from Earth.
- And your father?

11:06.571 --> 11:09.646
He ain't from Missouri.
That's all I know.

11:10.118 --> 11:11.994
I see it within you.

11:11.994 --> 11:15.303
An unorthodox genealogy

11:15.970 --> 11:20.095
A hybrid that seems particularly...

11:21.550 --> 11:23.316
Desleixado.

11:24.426 --> 11:28.324
You know, they told me you people
were conceited douchebags.

11:28.875 --> 11:30.867
But that isn't true at all..

11:37.424 --> 11:39.909
Ah, shit. I'm using my wrong
eye again, aren't I?

11:39.909 --> 11:43.255
I'm sorry, that was...that was
meant to be behind your back.

11:44.767 --> 11:46.877
Count yourself blessed
they didn't kill you.

11:47.258 --> 11:50.566
You're telling me.
You want to buy some batteries??

12:04.831 --> 12:08.871
All right, let's get baldly to Xandar
and collect that bounty.

13:07.417 --> 13:09.511
Aquelas coisas
sobre meu pai.

13:09.910 --> 13:11.912
Who does she think she is?

13:11.912 --> 13:14.134
I know you're sensitive about that.

13:14.847 --> 13:17.701
I'm not sensitive about it.
I just don't know who he is.

13:19.227 --> 13:22.118
Sorry if it seemed like I was
flirting with the High Priestess.

13:22.823 --> 13:25.733
- I wasn't.
- I don't care if you were.

13:26.785 --> 13:28.803
Well I feel like you do care.

13:28.803 --> 13:31.814
That's why I'm apologizing.
So, sorry.

13:32.178 --> 13:34.665
Gamora is not the one for you, Quill.

13:35.791 --> 13:36.839
Damn shadow.

13:36.839 --> 13:38.911
There are two types of
beings in the universe.

13:39.264 --> 13:42.352
Those who dance and
those who do not.

13:43.857 --> 13:45.905
I first met my beloved
at a war rally.

13:46.356 --> 13:50.821
- Oh god.
- Everyone in the village flailed about dancing.

13:50.821 --> 13:54.532
Except one woman.
My Ovette.

13:55.386 --> 13:57.705
I knew immediately she
was the one for me.

13:58.003 --> 14:01.139
The most melodic song in the
world could be playing..

14:01.460 --> 14:03.820
She wouldn't even tap her foot.

14:04.910 --> 14:06.681
Wouldn't move a muscle.

14:07.404 --> 14:10.186
One might assume she was dead.

14:10.529 --> 14:12.637
That does sound pretty hot.

14:12.912 --> 14:15.435
It would make my nether-regions engorged.

14:15.736 --> 14:17.732
Okay I get it, yes.

14:18.175 --> 14:20.215
I'm a dancer, Gamora is not.

14:20.527 --> 14:23.235
You just need to find a woman
who is pathetic,

14:23.880 --> 14:25.290
like you.

14:30.581 --> 14:33.603
I'm hungry.
Hand me some of that Yaro root.

14:33.603 --> 14:35.442
N�o, ainda n�o est� madura.

14:35.442 --> 14:37.858
- ...and I hate you.
- You hate me?

14:38.173 --> 14:40.945
You left me there while you
stole that stone for yourself.

14:41.460 --> 14:43.956
And yet here you
stand, a hero.

14:43.956 --> 14:47.737
I will be free of these shackles
soon and I will kill you.

14:48.076 --> 14:50.650
- I swear.
- No.

14:50.650 --> 14:54.145
You're gonna live out the rest of
your days in a prison on Xandar,

14:54.709 --> 14:56.910
wishing you could.

15:02.915 --> 15:05.532
This is weird. We've got a Sovereign fleet
approaching from the rear.

15:05.532 --> 15:08.202
- Why would they do that?
- Perhaps because Rocket stole some of their batteries.

15:08.202 --> 15:09.830
Dude!

15:09.830 --> 15:11.965
Right.
He didn't steal some of those.

15:11.965 --> 15:14.003
I don't know why they're after us.
What a mystery this is.

15:23.978 --> 15:25.634
What were you thinking?

15:25.634 --> 15:27.350
Dude, they were really
easy to steal!

15:27.350 --> 15:28.929
- That's your defense?
- Come on!

15:28.929 --> 15:31.456
You saw how that High Priestess
talked down to us.

15:31.456 --> 15:33.275
Now I'm teaching her a lesson!

15:33.618 --> 15:36.270
Oh, I didn't realize your
motivation was altruism.

15:36.270 --> 15:38.874
It's really a shame the Sovereign
have mistaken your intentions...

15:38.874 --> 15:40.630
- ...and are trying to kill us.
- Exactly!

15:40.630 --> 15:42.414
- I was being sarcastic!!
- No!

15:42.414 --> 15:44.536
You're supposed to use the sarcastic tone!

15:44.536 --> 15:47.055
- Now I look foolish!
- Can we put the bickering on hold...

15:47.055 --> 15:49.074
...'til after we've survived
this massive space battlel?

15:49.074 --> 15:50.583
- More incoming!
- Good!

15:50.583 --> 15:52.636
I want to kill some guys!

15:59.351 --> 16:00.557
You're not killing anyone.

16:00.557 --> 16:02.581
All those ships are remotely piloted.

16:05.387 --> 16:07.028
Dammit!

16:15.973 --> 16:18.046
What is the delay, Admiral?

16:18.046 --> 16:21.679
High Priestess, the batteries,
they are exceptionally combustible...

16:21.679 --> 16:23.066
...and could destroy the entire fleet.

16:23.066 --> 16:26.362
Our concern is their slight
against our people.

16:26.362 --> 16:29.772
We hired them and
they steal from us.

16:30.494 --> 16:33.237
It's heresy of the highest order.

16:33.752 --> 16:36.096
All command modules...

16:36.096 --> 16:38.573
...fire with the intent to kill.

16:46.840 --> 16:48.834
What's the nearest
habitable planet?

16:49.732 --> 16:51.117
It's called Berhert.

16:51.117 --> 16:52.711
- How many jumps?
- Only one.

16:52.711 --> 16:55.562
But the access point is
47 clicks away.

16:55.562 --> 16:58.889
And you have to go through
that quantum asteroid field.

17:06.812 --> 17:08.494
Quill, to make it through that...

17:08.494 --> 17:10.053
...you'd have to be the
greatest pilot in the universe.

17:10.053 --> 17:11.381
Lucky for us...

17:11.381 --> 17:13.620
- I...
- I am.

17:24.508 --> 17:27.399
- What are you doing?
- I've been flying this rig since I was 10 years old.

17:27.399 --> 17:30.485
I was cybernetically engineered
to pilot a spacecraft.

17:30.485 --> 17:32.975
You were cybernetically engineered
to be a douchebag!

17:32.975 --> 17:34.995
- Stop it!
- Quill, later on tonight,

17:34.995 --> 17:38.188
you're gonna be laying down in your bed and there's
gonna be something squishy in your pillowcase.

17:38.188 --> 17:42.242
And you're gonna be like, What's this?
And it's gonna be because I put a turd in there.

17:42.449 --> 17:45.145
You put your turd in my bed,
I shave you.

17:45.145 --> 17:48.273
Oh, it won't be my turd.
It'll be Drax's

17:50.415 --> 17:52.602
I have famously huge turds.

17:52.602 --> 17:55.265
We're about to die, and
this is what we're discussing?

17:56.597 --> 17:58.173
Son of a...!

17:58.173 --> 17:59.949
Dude! Seriously!

17:59.949 --> 18:01.381
Hey, let me...

18:14.361 --> 18:15.769
Idiots!

18:15.769 --> 18:18.265
Ah! That's what you get when Quill flies.

18:19.717 --> 18:22.066
We still have a Sovereign craft behind us.

18:24.418 --> 18:26.220
Our weapons are down.

18:26.220 --> 18:28.414
Twenty clicks to the jump.

18:31.513 --> 18:32.997
Hold on.

18:41.728 --> 18:43.485
It's not ripe.

18:45.005 --> 18:46.694
<i>SPACESUITS FOR EMERGENCY
OR FOR FUN.</i>

18:50.996 --> 18:53.553
Come on, Zylak.
You can do this.

18:56.629 --> 18:57.629
Yes!

18:58.667 --> 19:00.593
15 clicks to the jump!

19:19.052 --> 19:20.856
10 clicks!

19:24.041 --> 19:26.481
Die, spaceship!

19:31.216 --> 19:34.042
- You suck, Zylak.
- Typical.

19:36.769 --> 19:37.939
It's 5 clicks!

19:44.583 --> 19:45.868
Son of a...!

19:46.214 --> 19:48.470
They went around the field!

20:02.853 --> 20:05.783
Someone destroyed all our ships!

20:05.783 --> 20:07.379
What?

20:10.901 --> 20:12.472
Who?

20:13.507 --> 20:14.991
1 click!

20:15.961 --> 20:18.260
- What is that?
- Who cares?

20:18.471 --> 20:20.748
That's the jump point!
Go, go!

20:23.899 --> 20:25.253
It's a guy.

20:33.841 --> 20:36.101
Oh my god.
He's still out there?

21:05.227 --> 21:07.264
Groot, put your seatbelt on!

21:08.284 --> 21:12.041
Prepare for a really bad landing!

21:41.398 --> 21:42.238
BERHERT

21:54.597 --> 21:56.674
That was awesome!

21:58.566 --> 22:00.240
Yes!

22:01.679 --> 22:02.867
Look at this!

22:03.816 --> 22:05.598
Where's the other half of our ship?

22:05.598 --> 22:06.773
My ship.

22:06.773 --> 22:09.797
Either one of you could've gotten
us through that field...

22:09.797 --> 22:13.270
...had you flown with what's between
your ears instead of what's between your legs!

22:14.761 --> 22:17.707
If what's between my legs
had a hand on it...

22:18.071 --> 22:20.162
...I guarantee I could've
landed this ship with it.

22:20.162 --> 22:23.673
Peter. We almost died because
of your arrogance.

22:23.673 --> 22:26.892
No, like, because he stole...
Anulax batteries.

22:26.892 --> 22:29.386
They're called Harbulary batteries.

22:29.386 --> 22:30.834
No, they're not!

22:31.085 --> 22:33.563
You know why I did it,
Star-Munch?  Hmm?

22:33.778 --> 22:35.375
I'm not gonna answer
to Star-Munch.

22:35.375 --> 22:38.451
- I did it because I wanted to!
- Dick.

22:38.451 --> 22:40.525
What are we even talking
about this for?

22:40.745 --> 22:44.223
We just had a little man save
us by blowing up 50 ships!

22:44.223 --> 22:47.142
- How little?
- I, I don't know, like this?

22:47.142 --> 22:49.380
A little one-inch man saved us?

22:49.380 --> 22:51.975
Well, if he got closer, I'm
sure he'd be much larger.

22:51.975 --> 22:54.459
That's how eyesight works,
you stupid raccoon.

22:54.459 --> 22:56.204
Don't call me a raccoon!

22:56.570 --> 22:59.199
I'm sorry.
I took it too far.

23:00.138 --> 23:02.092
I meant trash panda.

23:04.048 --> 23:05.202
Is that better?

23:05.893 --> 23:07.248
I don't know.

23:07.792 --> 23:10.218
It's worse.  It's so much worse.

23:10.420 --> 23:11.709
You son of a...!

23:12.583 --> 23:14.279
I've about had it with you!

23:14.533 --> 23:16.784
Someone followed you
through the jump point.

23:18.633 --> 23:21.042
Set me free.
You'll need my help.

23:21.405 --> 23:22.571
I'm not a fool, Nebula.

23:22.571 --> 23:24.448
You are a fool to deprive
yourself a hand in combat.

23:24.448 --> 23:26.972
- You'll attack me the moment I let you go.
- No I won't.

23:27.214 --> 23:30.663
You would think an evil super-villain
would learn how to properly lie.

23:31.182 --> 23:32.948
I bet it's the one-inch man.

24:06.696 --> 24:10.295
After all these years,
I've found you.

24:11.071 --> 24:12.540
And who the hell are you?

24:13.421 --> 24:16.418
I figured my rugged good looks
would make that obvious.

24:17.802 --> 24:19.798
My name is Ego.

24:21.018 --> 24:23.232
And I'm your dad, Peter.

24:26.773 --> 24:27.853
CONTRAXIA

24:37.808 --> 24:39.203
You know what they say.

24:39.203 --> 24:41.633
You're out of luck
until you've gone duck.

25:06.972 --> 25:08.715
<i>Yondu!</i>

25:09.692 --> 25:11.401
Come on down!

25:24.156 --> 25:26.545
...this woman, I ended up marrying her.

25:26.545 --> 25:28.898
I said, Aleta, I love you...

25:28.898 --> 25:30.559
...but you're losing your mind!

25:30.559 --> 25:32.279
And she's always been this way.

25:32.279 --> 25:34.278
I could never trust her, you know.

25:34.814 --> 25:35.895
Stakar.

25:39.200 --> 25:40.776
It's been some time.

25:44.784 --> 25:48.823
Seems like this establishment
is the wrong kind of disreputable.

25:54.802 --> 25:57.596
- Stakar.
- There's 100 Ravager factions.

25:57.596 --> 26:00.940
You just lost the business of 99
of them by serving one.

26:00.940 --> 26:04.268
- Please, sir. Please!
- Get away from me.

26:08.482 --> 26:10.809
You can go to hell then!

26:11.474 --> 26:13.717
I don't give a damn what
you think of me!

26:13.717 --> 26:15.420
So, what are you following us for?

26:15.420 --> 26:17.241
You're gonna listen to
what I gotta say!

26:17.241 --> 26:19.924
I don't gotta listen to nothing!
You betrayed the code!

26:19.924 --> 26:21.952
Ravagers don't deal in kids!

26:21.952 --> 26:24.915
I told you before!
I didn't know what was going on!

26:24.915 --> 26:27.130
You didn't know 'cause you didn't
want to know 'cause it made you rich.

26:27.130 --> 26:29.449
I demand a seat at the table.

26:29.449 --> 26:31.582
I wear these flames, same as you.

26:31.582 --> 26:32.953
You may dress like us...

26:32.953 --> 26:35.888
...but you'll never hear the Horns
of Freedom when you die, Yondu.

26:36.188 --> 26:38.118
And the Colors of Ogord...

26:38.118 --> 26:40.847
...will never lash over your grave.

26:42.292 --> 26:43.706
If you think...

26:44.960 --> 26:48.432
I take pleasure in exiling you...

26:49.352 --> 26:50.729
...you're wrong.

26:52.097 --> 26:54.246
You broke all our hearts.

27:09.381 --> 27:10.681
Pathetic.

27:11.990 --> 27:14.191
First, Quill betrays us...

27:14.191 --> 27:17.388
...and Yondu just lets
him go scot-free.

27:17.388 --> 27:19.050
We followed him...

27:19.050 --> 27:22.753
...because he was the one who wasn't
afraid to do what needed to be done.

27:22.753 --> 27:25.020
Seems he's going soft.

27:25.654 --> 27:28.339
If he's so soft,
why are you whispering for?

27:28.339 --> 27:30.526
You know I'm right, Kraglin.

27:30.526 --> 27:33.229
You best be very careful

27:33.229 --> 27:35.214
what you say about our captain.

27:35.415 --> 27:36.812
Who is that?

28:19.255 --> 28:21.137
Yondu Udonta.

28:21.652 --> 28:24.003
I have a proposition for you.

28:24.726 --> 28:28.904
I hired Yondu to pick you up when
your mother passed away.

28:28.904 --> 28:30.800
But, instead of returning you...

28:31.657 --> 28:33.005
...Yondu kept you.

28:33.618 --> 28:35.839
I have no clue as to why.

28:37.610 --> 28:38.972
Well, I'll tell you why.

28:39.420 --> 28:41.902
'Cause I was a skinny little kid who
could squeeze into places adults couldn't.

28:41.902 --> 28:44.160
It made it easier for thieving.

28:44.386 --> 28:48.026
Well. I've been trying to
track you down ever since.

28:48.270 --> 28:50.081
I thought Yondu was your father.

28:50.081 --> 28:52.612
What?  We've been together
this whole time...

28:52.612 --> 28:55.435
...and you thought Yondu was
my actual blood relative?

28:55.808 --> 28:58.997
- You look exactly alike.
- One's blue!

29:00.528 --> 29:02.521
No, he's not my father!

29:02.521 --> 29:04.523
Yondu is the guy
who abducted me.

29:04.523 --> 29:07.014
Kicked the crap out of me
so I could learn to fight.

29:07.014 --> 29:09.125
And kept me in terror by
threatening to eat me.

29:09.865 --> 29:11.373
- Eat you?
- Yeah.

29:11.373 --> 29:13.325
Ah, that son of a bitch!

29:13.995 --> 29:15.577
How did you locate us now?

29:16.140 --> 29:19.309
Well, even where I reside, out
past the edge what's known...

29:19.309 --> 29:22.030
...we've heard tales about the
man they call Star-Lord.

29:22.030 --> 29:23.832
What say we head out there right now?

29:24.361 --> 29:25.964
Your associates are welcome.

29:25.964 --> 29:28.188
Even that triangle-face monkey, there.

29:28.746 --> 29:30.046
I promise you...

29:30.341 --> 29:33.073
...it's not like any other
place you've ever seen.

29:33.473 --> 29:34.602
And there,

29:35.058 --> 29:39.521
I can explain your very
special heritage.

29:40.684 --> 29:44.912
Finally get to be the father
I've always wanted to be.

29:47.154 --> 29:48.454
Excuse me.

29:49.357 --> 29:50.657
I've gotta take a whiz.

29:57.306 --> 29:58.606
I'm not buying it.

30:01.571 --> 30:03.075
Let's go take a walk.

30:10.399 --> 30:11.945
I am Mantis.

30:16.205 --> 30:17.837
What are you doing?

30:17.837 --> 30:19.138
Smiling.

30:19.851 --> 30:22.950
I hear it is the thing to do
to make people like you.

30:23.972 --> 30:25.719
Not if you do it like that.

30:27.939 --> 30:30.928
Oh.
I was raised alone on Ego's planet.

30:30.928 --> 30:35.325
I do not understand the
intricacies of social interaction.

30:37.941 --> 30:39.808
Can I pet your puppy?

30:39.808 --> 30:41.355
It's adorable.

30:45.132 --> 30:46.432
Yes.

30:56.154 --> 30:59.994
That is called a practical joke!

31:02.788 --> 31:05.982
I liked it very much!

31:06.215 --> 31:08.139
I just made it up.

31:11.094 --> 31:12.562
Give me a break!

31:12.799 --> 31:15.044
After all this time, you're gonna
show up and just all of a sudden...

31:15.044 --> 31:16.895
- ...you want to be my dad?
- I hear you.

31:16.895 --> 31:18.795
You know, by the way,
this could be a trap.

31:18.795 --> 31:22.799
Ok? The Kree ~Perus, the
Ravagers, they all want us dead.

31:22.799 --> 31:24.766
- I know, but...
- But what?

31:24.766 --> 31:27.555
What was that story you told
me about Zardu Hasselfrau?

31:27.555 --> 31:30.274
- Who?
- He owned a magic boat.

31:32.289 --> 31:34.310
- David Hasselhoff?
- Right.

31:34.310 --> 31:36.864
Not in a magic boat.
A talking car.

31:36.864 --> 31:38.324
Why did he talk, again?

31:38.324 --> 31:41.859
To help him fight crime,
and to be supportive.

31:41.859 --> 31:44.695
As a child, you would carry
his picture in your pocket...

31:44.695 --> 31:46.562
and you would tell all
the other children...

31:46.562 --> 31:49.051
...that he was your father,
but that he was out of town..

31:49.051 --> 31:51.248
Shooting Knight Rider or touring
with his band in Germany.

31:51.248 --> 31:53.486
I told you that when I was drunk.
Why are you bringing it up now?

31:53.486 --> 31:56.114
- I love that story.
- I hate that story.

31:56.540 --> 31:58.023
It's so sad!

31:58.533 --> 32:02.750
As a kid, I used to see all the other
kids all playing catch with their dad.

32:02.750 --> 32:05.637
And I wanted that, more than
anything in the world.

32:05.637 --> 32:07.728
That's my point, Peter.

32:08.241 --> 32:11.292
What if this man
is your Hasselhoff?

32:13.255 --> 32:16.075
Listen.  If he ends
up being evil...

32:17.073 --> 32:18.687
...we'll just kill him.

32:25.527 --> 32:27.460
You're leaving me with that fox?

32:27.460 --> 32:28.905
He's not a fox.

32:28.905 --> 32:30.866
Shoot her if she does
anything suspicious.

32:31.772 --> 32:34.022
- Or if you feel like it.
- Okay.

32:34.853 --> 32:36.807
Hey. It'll be just a
couple of days.

32:36.807 --> 32:39.502
We'll be back before Rocket's
finished fixing the ship.

32:42.875 --> 32:44.119
What if Sovereign come?

32:44.119 --> 32:46.553
There's no way for them to
know we're here.  Let's go.

32:46.553 --> 32:47.992
I'm uncertain about parting ways.

32:47.992 --> 32:49.591
God, you're like an old woman.

32:49.830 --> 32:51.320
Because I'm wise?

32:52.386 --> 32:54.198
Why do you have so much luggage?

32:54.198 --> 32:56.480
I don't want Groot
playing with my things.

32:59.183 --> 33:01.171
I hope daddy isn't as big of a
dick as you,

33:01.171 --> 33:02.472
Orphan Boy.

33:03.458 --> 33:05.350
What is your goal here?

33:05.663 --> 33:07.357
To get everbody to hate you?

33:07.611 --> 33:09.248
Because it's working.

33:53.364 --> 33:55.481
Hey. Can I ask you a
personal question?

33:57.101 --> 33:59.570
Oh! Noone has ever asked
me a personal question.

33:59.570 --> 34:01.499
Your antennae, what are they for?

34:01.499 --> 34:02.909
Their purpose?

34:02.909 --> 34:05.151
Yes, Quill and I have a bet.

34:05.539 --> 34:07.161
- Ugh. You're not supposed to say that.
- I say...

34:07.514 --> 34:10.551
that if you're about to go through
a doorway that's too low...

34:10.994 --> 34:13.756
...the antennae will feel this and
keep you from being decapitated.

34:13.756 --> 34:15.762
Right.
And if it's anything other than...

34:15.762 --> 34:18.359
...you specifically not being
decapitated by a doorway,

34:18.359 --> 34:19.228
I win.

34:19.228 --> 34:21.818
They are not for feeling doorways.

34:23.204 --> 34:25.405
I think...

34:25.405 --> 34:27.418
...they have something to do
with my empathic abilities.

34:27.418 --> 34:28.527
What are those?

34:28.527 --> 34:30.318
If I touch someone,

34:30.318 --> 34:32.511
I can
feel their feelings.

34:32.511 --> 34:34.330
- You read minds?
- No.

34:34.330 --> 34:36.799
Telepaths know thoughts.

34:36.799 --> 34:39.100
Empaths feel feelings.

34:40.209 --> 34:41.509
Emotions.

34:43.342 --> 34:44.646
May I?

34:45.556 --> 34:46.856
Oh, all right.

34:54.512 --> 34:57.022
You feel love.

34:58.340 --> 35:01.179
Yeah, I guess feel a general
unselfish love for just about everybody...

35:01.179 --> 35:02.480
No!

35:02.480 --> 35:05.507
- Romantic, sexual love.
- No, no, I don't.

35:05.507 --> 35:07.276
- For her!
- No!

35:07.276 --> 35:08.577
That is not...

35:09.974 --> 35:11.274
Okay.

35:14.248 --> 35:17.502
She just told everyone
your deepest, darkest secret!

35:17.502 --> 35:19.673
Dude, come on, I think you're
overreacting a little bit.

35:19.673 --> 35:22.132
You must be so embarrassed!

35:24.826 --> 35:27.462
Do me!
Do me! Do me!

35:33.537 --> 35:36.816
I have never felt such humor.

35:40.663 --> 35:42.997
So unbelievably not cool.

35:48.354 --> 35:52.650
Touch me, and the only thing you're
gonna feel is a broken jaw.

35:58.697 --> 36:03.103
I can also alter emotions,
to some extent.

36:03.103 --> 36:04.467
Yeah, like what?

36:04.743 --> 36:06.993
If I touch someone who is sad...

36:07.409 --> 36:11.058
...I can ease them into
contentment for a short while.

36:11.440 --> 36:15.030
I can make a stubborn person compliant.

36:15.789 --> 36:18.936
But I mostly use it to
help my master sleep.

36:19.214 --> 36:24.079
He lies awake at night
thinking about his progeny.

36:25.871 --> 36:27.338
Do one of those on me.

36:32.106 --> 36:33.516
Sleep.

37:37.147 --> 37:38.700
I love this song.

38:10.439 --> 38:11.739
There.

39:27.941 --> 39:30.549
Ain't so tough now,
without all your toys.

39:30.549 --> 39:31.850
Are ya?

39:34.909 --> 39:36.209
Move!

39:51.627 --> 39:52.927
Crap.

39:58.116 --> 40:01.980
- Hey there, rat!!
- How's it going, you blue idiot?

40:02.237 --> 40:03.925
Not so bad.

40:04.325 --> 40:06.686
We got ourselves a pretty
good little gig here.

40:06.686 --> 40:10.067
This golden gal with quite a
high opinion of herself...

40:10.067 --> 40:13.478
...has offered us a large sum to
deliver you and your pals over to her...

40:13.478 --> 40:15.382
...'cause she wants to kill y'all.

40:16.049 --> 40:17.438
Your Friend...

40:17.438 --> 40:19.191
There's too many of them.

40:19.191 --> 40:22.457
He needs my help.
If you care about him....

40:22.457 --> 40:25.464
...you need to get
me out of these bonds.

40:25.464 --> 40:27.264
They are going to kill him!

40:27.264 --> 40:29.643
I'll tell you, it was
pretty easy to find you.

40:29.643 --> 40:31.013
I put a tracer on
your ship back there...

40:31.013 --> 40:33.174
...during the war with Xandar.

40:33.174 --> 40:35.201
Give me your word you
won't hurt Groot...

40:35.201 --> 40:37.765
...and I'll tell you
where the batteries are.

40:38.416 --> 40:41.116
Lucky for you, my
word don't mean squat.

40:41.116 --> 40:43.931
Otherwise, I'd actually hand you over.

40:43.931 --> 40:45.824
Otherwise...what?

40:45.824 --> 40:47.525
We'll take them batteries.

40:47.525 --> 40:50.706
They're worth, what, a
quarter mil on the open market?

40:50.706 --> 40:53.290
That Priestess offered
us a million.

40:53.290 --> 40:55.708
A quarter is only one third of that!

40:55.940 --> 40:57.349
A quarter ain't a third.

40:57.349 --> 40:59.221
A quarter is 25.

40:59.221 --> 40:59.787
No.

40:59.787 --> 41:02.768
We can't even buy a pair
of boots with 25 units.

41:02.768 --> 41:06.518
Enough! The point is, we ain't stupid enough

41:06.518 --> 41:08.753
to help kill the Guardians of the Galaxy!

41:08.753 --> 41:11.300
The whole dang Nova Corps'd be on us.

41:11.300 --> 41:13.047
That ain't right!

41:13.597 --> 41:16.294
I just gotta say it this
one time, captain.

41:16.784 --> 41:19.319
No matter how many times
Quill betrays you...

41:19.319 --> 41:22.370
...you protect him like none
of the rest of us much matter.

41:23.082 --> 41:26.050
- I'm the one what sticks up for you!!
- Take it easy, Kraglin.

41:26.050 --> 41:28.753
Damn straight, lads.
He's gone soft.

41:28.753 --> 41:32.054
I suppose it's time for
a change in leadership.

41:37.375 --> 41:39.775
Put your ~gob guns down!

41:39.775 --> 41:43.073
There must be some kind of
peaceful resolution to this, fellas.

41:43.073 --> 41:45.940
Or even a violent one, where
I'm standing over there.

42:04.103 --> 42:05.903
Well, hello boys.

42:11.208 --> 42:12.808
It's not ripe.

42:33.649 --> 42:35.329
EGO'S PLANET

42:59.410 --> 43:02.730
Welcome, everyone, to my world.

43:04.665 --> 43:06.253
Wow. You have your own planet?

43:06.253 --> 43:09.614
Come on.  It's no larger
than your Earth's moon.

43:10.008 --> 43:11.308
Humility.

43:11.610 --> 43:12.910
I like it.

43:13.482 --> 43:16.162
I, too, am extraordinarily humble.

44:00.742 --> 44:03.678
You own a planet and can destroy
two dozen spaceships

44:03.678 --> 44:04.979
without a suit.

44:05.720 --> 44:07.320
What are you exactly?

44:08.679 --> 44:12.179
I'm what's called a Celestial, sweetheart.

44:13.849 --> 44:16.749
A Celestial, like a God?

44:17.595 --> 44:19.984
Oh, a small "g", son.

44:20.294 --> 44:21.994
At least on the days I'm

44:21.994 --> 44:23.425
feeling as humble as Drax.

44:38.526 --> 44:42.106
I don't know where I came from, exactly.

44:42.106 --> 44:44.837
The first thing I remember is...

44:44.837 --> 44:47.428
...flickering. Adrift in
the cosmos, utterly...

44:47.922 --> 44:50.722
...and entirely alone.

44:51.809 --> 44:53.789
Over millions of years...

44:53.789 --> 44:57.700
...I learned to control
the molecules around me.

44:57.700 --> 45:01.241
I grew smarter and stronger.

45:03.514 --> 45:06.714
And I continued building from there.

45:06.714 --> 45:08.815
Layer by layer...

45:08.815 --> 45:11.766
...the very planet you walk on now.

45:14.067 --> 45:15.567
But I wanted more.

45:16.491 --> 45:17.791
I desired...

45:18.878 --> 45:20.178
...meaning.

45:21.205 --> 45:25.321
There must be some life out
there in the universe...

45:25.321 --> 45:28.302
...besides just me, I thought.

45:28.302 --> 45:32.390
And so, I set myself the task
of finding it.

45:33.275 --> 45:34.875
I created...

45:34.875 --> 45:38.556
...what I imagined biological
life to be like...

45:38.556 --> 45:42.587
...down to the most minute detail.

45:43.993 --> 45:45.493
Did you make a penis?

45:45.493 --> 45:48.200
- Dude!
- What is wrong with you?

45:48.200 --> 45:49.641
If he is a planet,

45:49.641 --> 45:51.942
how could he
make a baby with your mother?

45:51.942 --> 45:53.736
He would smush her!

45:55.177 --> 45:57.777
I...ugh!  I don't need to hear
how my parents...

45:58.855 --> 46:00.155
Why?

46:00.675 --> 46:03.455
My father would tell the story of
impregnating my mother

46:03.455 --> 46:05.726
- every winter solstice.
- That's disgusting.

46:05.726 --> 46:07.657
It was beautiful.

46:09.373 --> 46:11.273
You Earthers have hang-ups.

46:11.273 --> 46:12.623
Yes, Drax.

46:12.623 --> 46:13.924
I got a penis.

46:14.537 --> 46:15.837
Thank you.

46:15.837 --> 46:17.338
And it's not half bad.

46:17.980 --> 46:19.510
I also have

46:19.510 --> 46:22.411
pain receptors
and a digestive system...

46:22.411 --> 46:24.732
...and all the accompanying junk.

46:25.127 --> 46:29.897
I wanted to experience what it
truly meant to be human.

46:30.228 --> 46:33.242
As I set out amongst the stars...

46:34.125 --> 46:36.225
...'til I found...

46:36.225 --> 46:37.727
...what I sought.

46:39.416 --> 46:40.716
Life.

46:42.362 --> 46:45.662
I was not alone in the
universe after all.

46:50.609 --> 46:52.409
When did you meet my mother?

46:55.951 --> 46:57.651
Not long after.

47:02.858 --> 47:04.870
It was, with Meredith,

47:04.870 --> 47:07.718
that I
first experienced love.

47:08.375 --> 47:13.365
I called her my River Lily.

47:17.427 --> 47:19.747
And from that love, Peter...

47:22.886 --> 47:24.186
You.

47:30.534 --> 47:33.834
I've searched for you for so long.

47:35.175 --> 47:36.865
And when I heard of
a man from Earth...

47:36.865 --> 47:40.326
...who held an Infinity Stone
in his hand without dying...

47:41.319 --> 47:45.019
...I knew you must be the
son of the woman I loved.

47:46.114 --> 47:48.434
If you loved her, why
did you leave her?

48:25.584 --> 48:27.864
Sorry about this!

48:58.827 --> 49:02.180
Captain! Help me!
Please help!

49:02.180 --> 49:03.427
Captain!

49:06.627 --> 49:08.827
You're the one what killed those men...

49:08.827 --> 49:11.128
...by leading them
down the wrong path.

49:11.128 --> 49:12.829
Because you're weak.

49:14.935 --> 49:16.335
And stupid.

49:18.217 --> 49:20.591
It's time for the Ravagers...

49:20.591 --> 49:24.421
...to rise once again to glory
with a new captain...

49:24.421 --> 49:25.621
Taserface!

49:33.468 --> 49:36.083
I'm sorry.
Your name is...

49:36.083 --> 49:37.472
It's Taserface?

49:38.200 --> 49:39.162
That's right.

49:39.162 --> 49:42.363
Do you shoot tasers
out of your face?

49:42.363 --> 49:44.722
It's metaphorical!

49:48.255 --> 49:49.555
For what?

49:49.804 --> 49:51.400
For...

49:51.400 --> 49:54.101
It is a name what strikes fear...

49:54.101 --> 49:56.665
...into the hearts of
anyone what hears it!

49:58.797 --> 50:00.391
Okay...

50:00.391 --> 50:02.892
Whatever you say.

50:03.479 --> 50:05.699
You shut up.
You're next.

50:06.633 --> 50:10.901
Udonta, I've been
waiting a long time to...

50:11.388 --> 50:12.202
What?

50:13.390 --> 50:16.343
I'm sorry.
I am so sorry.

50:17.064 --> 50:20.134
I just keep imagining
you waking up in the morning, sir...

50:20.134 --> 50:23.668
...looking in the mirror and,
in all seriousness, saying to yourself...

50:23.668 --> 50:27.334
"You know what would be a really
kick-ass name?

50:27.334 --> 50:29.327
Taserface!".

50:30.811 --> 50:33.401
That's how I hear you in my head!

50:33.401 --> 50:34.890
I can't take it anymore!

50:34.890 --> 50:37.166
What was your second choice?

50:37.166 --> 50:38.837
Scrotum Hat?

50:41.691 --> 50:44.901
New plan.
We're killing you first.

50:44.901 --> 50:46.207
Well...

50:46.207 --> 50:48.482
Dying is certainly better

50:48.482 --> 50:51.425
than having to live an entire life...

50:51.425 --> 50:54.270
...as a moronic shitbag who thinks
Taserface is a cool name.

50:54.476 --> 50:57.156
That's enough killing for today.

51:01.563 --> 51:03.412
She's the daughter of Thanos.

51:06.602 --> 51:09.095
I thought you were the biggest
sadist in the galaxy.

51:09.095 --> 51:11.282
That was when daddy was
paying my bills.

51:12.353 --> 51:15.083
The Priestess wants to
kill the fox herself.

51:15.775 --> 51:17.575
And he has bounties on his head

51:17.575 --> 51:20.039
in at least 12 Kree provinces.

51:21.646 --> 51:23.307
I assure you...

51:23.307 --> 51:26.574
I am not as easy a mark as an
old man without his magic stick...

51:26.574 --> 51:28.678
...or a talking woodland beast.

51:30.232 --> 51:32.340
I want ten percent of the take.

51:34.309 --> 51:36.579
And a couple more things.

51:38.131 --> 51:39.894
We got a whole box of hands...

51:39.894 --> 51:42.011
- ...if that one don't work out.
- It is fine.

51:43.722 --> 51:46.286
You, uh, think them Kree is
gonna execute the captain?

51:46.286 --> 51:50.107
The Kree consider themselves
merciful.  It will be painless.

51:51.189 --> 51:54.804
Well, uh, here it is.
It's the best ship we got.

51:55.272 --> 51:57.091
The location of Ego's planet
in the nav.

51:57.091 --> 51:59.631
We'll wire you the ten percent
once we's paid.

52:00.157 --> 52:02.175
What're you gonna do
with your share?

52:03.185 --> 52:07.291
As a child, my father would have Gamora
and me battle one another in training.

52:08.695 --> 52:10.821
Every time my sister prevailed...

52:11.444 --> 52:14.622
...my father would replace a
piece of me with machinery...

52:15.267 --> 52:18.439
...claiming he wanted me
to be her equal.

52:19.661 --> 52:21.584
But she won.

52:21.584 --> 52:24.706
Again and again and again,

52:24.706 --> 52:27.385
never once refraining.

52:28.970 --> 52:32.770
So, after I murder my sister...
I will buy a warship

52:32.770 --> 52:35.227
with every
conceivable instrument of death.

52:35.528 --> 52:39.231
I will hunt my father like a
dog and I will tear him apart slowly...

52:39.742 --> 52:41.487
piece by piece,

52:41.487 --> 52:45.534
until he knows some semblance
of the profound and unceasing pain...

52:45.534 --> 52:48.637
...I know every single day.

52:50.810 --> 52:51.530
Yeah...

52:52.864 --> 52:55.505
...I was talking about
a pretty necklace.

52:55.984 --> 52:57.968
Or a nice hat, you know.

52:57.968 --> 53:01.188
Something to make the other
girls go, Ooooh, that's nice.

53:05.497 --> 53:09.186
Anyways, happy trails.

53:17.777 --> 53:21.330
My mother told everyone my
father was from the stars.

53:23.690 --> 53:26.545
She had brain cancer, so
everyone thought she was delusional.

53:26.545 --> 53:29.060
- Peter.
- Listen, I'd love to believe
all of this, I really would,

53:29.060 --> 53:34.678
But you left the most wonderful
woman ever,

53:35.132 --> 53:36.585
to die alone.

53:36.585 --> 53:40.487
I didn't want to leave
your mother, Peter.

53:40.487 --> 53:43.379
If I don't return regularly
to my planet...

53:43.379 --> 53:44.873
...and the light within it...

53:44.873 --> 53:46.981
...this form will wither and perish.

53:46.981 --> 53:49.181
Then why didn't you come back?
Why did you send Yondu?

53:49.181 --> 53:51.942
A criminal, of all people, to
come and to fetch me.

53:51.942 --> 53:54.052
I loved your mother, Peter!

53:54.052 --> 53:56.978
I couldn't stand to step
foot on an Earth...

53:56.978 --> 54:00.553
...where she wasn't living!
You can't imagine what that's like!

54:00.553 --> 54:02.733
I know exactly what that feels like!

54:03.348 --> 54:05.744
I had to watch her die!

54:10.335 --> 54:15.296
Over the millions and millions
of years of my existence...

54:15.296 --> 54:17.552
...I've made many mistakes, Peter.

54:18.626 --> 54:20.835
But you're not one of them.

54:22.952 --> 54:27.314
Please give me the chance to be
the father she would want me to be.

54:32.610 --> 54:36.239
There's so much that I need to

54:36.239 --> 54:37.966
teach you about this planet...

54:38.822 --> 54:40.737
...and the light within.

54:40.737 --> 54:43.714
They are a part of you, Peter.

54:45.404 --> 54:47.005
What do you mean?

54:48.149 --> 54:50.056
Give me your hand, son.

54:51.292 --> 54:52.448
Here.

54:53.733 --> 54:55.762
Hold them like that.

54:58.875 --> 55:00.176
Now,

55:02.155 --> 55:05.179
close your eyes
and concentrate.

55:06.930 --> 55:09.724
Take your brain to the
center of this planet.

55:14.657 --> 55:17.029
Yes! Yes!

55:17.029 --> 55:19.263
- Yes!
- What was it?

55:19.688 --> 55:21.754
It's okay, just relax.
Concentrate.

55:21.754 --> 55:23.870
You can do it.
Bring it back.

55:24.226 --> 55:25.532
Yes!

55:26.253 --> 55:29.679
Now, shape it.

55:29.679 --> 55:31.253
Feel that energy.

55:35.591 --> 55:36.991
Yes.

55:40.646 --> 55:42.246
You're home.

55:44.502 --> 55:45.891
Peter...

56:19.038 --> 56:22.252
How'd you get to this
weird, dumb planet?

56:22.940 --> 56:24.935
Ego found me in my larvae state.

56:24.935 --> 56:27.075
Orphan on my homeworld.

56:27.882 --> 56:31.718
He raised me by hand and
kept me as his own.

56:31.718 --> 56:33.702
So, you're a pet.

56:34.191 --> 56:36.023
I suppose.

56:37.039 --> 56:39.312
People usually want cute pets.

56:39.312 --> 56:41.781
Why would Ego want such
a hideous one?

56:41.781 --> 56:43.178
I am hideous?

56:43.178 --> 56:46.058
You are horrifying to look at, yes.

56:48.421 --> 56:50.051
But that's a good thing.

56:51.017 --> 56:52.753
When you're ugly and
someone loves you...

56:52.753 --> 56:54.721
...you know they love
you for who you are.

56:56.337 --> 56:58.573
Beautiful people never
know who to trust.

56:58.573 --> 57:02.014
Well, then I am certainly
grateful to be ugly.

57:03.763 --> 57:06.913
Those pools, they remind
me of a time...

57:06.913 --> 57:10.303
...when I took my daughter to the
Forgotten Lakes of my homeworld.

57:11.625 --> 57:13.252
She was like you.

57:13.252 --> 57:14.762
Disgusting?

57:15.667 --> 57:17.083
Innocent.

57:49.524 --> 57:51.054
Drax?

57:51.288 --> 57:53.401
There's something I
must tell you.

58:01.580 --> 58:04.688
- What's going on?
- This gross bug lady
is my new friend.

58:04.688 --> 58:08.012
I'm learning many things,
like I'm a pet and ugly.

58:08.397 --> 58:10.360
You're not ugly.
Drax.

58:10.360 --> 58:12.496
- What are you talking about?
- Mantis,

58:12.496 --> 58:14.892
Can you show us where
we'll be staying?

58:15.552 --> 58:17.592
Why are there no other
beings on this planet?

58:17.592 --> 58:19.599
The planet is Ego.

58:19.599 --> 58:22.490
A dog would not invite a
flea to live on his back.

58:22.490 --> 58:23.993
And you're not a flea?

58:23.993 --> 58:25.977
I'm a flea with a purpose.

58:26.771 --> 58:28.489
I help him sleep.

58:29.503 --> 58:32.876
What were you about to say
to Drax before I walked out?

58:37.613 --> 58:38.736
Nothing.

58:39.246 --> 58:41.246
Your quarters are this way.

58:48.708 --> 58:51.346
We deliver you to
the Kree in the morning.

58:54.204 --> 58:57.334
Neither one of you will last
much longer after that.

58:57.998 --> 58:59.624
Okay, Taserface.

59:00.582 --> 59:04.514
Hey, tell the other guys, we said...
"Hi, Taserface."

59:09.279 --> 59:11.891
Oh! Hey, what about this little plant?
Can I smash it with a rock?

59:11.891 --> 59:13.320
No, Gef.

59:13.320 --> 59:15.120
It's too adorable to kill.

59:15.120 --> 59:16.774
Take it to the tailor.

59:18.516 --> 59:21.536
No offense, but your employees
are a bunch of jerks.

59:24.076 --> 59:27.197
I was a Kree battle slave for
20 years

59:27.197 --> 59:29.340
when Stakar freed me.

59:30.657 --> 59:33.484
He offered me a place with the Ravagers.

59:33.985 --> 59:37.819
He said, all I needed to do
was adhere to the code.

59:38.405 --> 59:39.783
But I was young...

59:41.012 --> 59:44.495
...and greedy and stupid.

59:45.190 --> 59:47.372
Like you stealing those batteries.

59:47.372 --> 59:49.018
That was mostly Drax.

59:50.467 --> 59:53.639
Me & Stakar, and the other captains...

59:54.767 --> 59:57.371
...we weren't so different from
you and your friends.

59:57.861 --> 01:00:00.240
The only family I ever had.

01:00:00.861 --> 01:00:02.852
When I broke the code...

01:00:05.086 --> 01:00:06.928
...they exiled me.

01:00:07.664 --> 01:00:09.448
This is what I deserve.

01:00:09.448 --> 01:00:11.467
Slow down, drama queen.

01:00:11.467 --> 01:00:14.475
You might deserve this, but I don't.
We gotta get out of here.

01:00:16.156 --> 01:00:17.816
Where's Quill?

01:00:17.816 --> 01:00:20.565
Ah, he went off with his old man.

01:00:20.565 --> 01:00:22.583
- Ego?
- Yeah.

01:00:22.583 --> 01:00:24.866
It's a day for dumb-ass names.

01:00:27.387 --> 01:00:30.318
You smiled, there for a second,
I got a warm feeling.

01:00:30.318 --> 01:00:33.010
But then it was ruined by
those disgusting-ass teeth.

01:00:33.010 --> 01:00:35.383
You're like, a professional
asshole, or what?

01:00:35.383 --> 01:00:36.684
Pretty much a pro.

01:00:36.684 --> 01:00:39.541
Why didn't you deliver Quill
to Ego like you promised?

01:00:40.332 --> 01:00:41.820
He was skinny.

01:00:42.316 --> 01:00:44.428
He fit into places we couldn't.

01:00:45.151 --> 01:00:46.987
Good for thieving.

01:00:52.047 --> 01:00:54.821
I got an idea on how
to get out of here.

01:00:56.293 --> 01:00:58.397
But we're gonna need
your little friend.

01:00:59.952 --> 01:01:03.453
Mascot! Mascot!
Mascot! (repeating)

01:01:13.079 --> 01:01:15.993
You fellas all want
~sausage drunk?

01:01:22.489 --> 01:01:25.373
Look how cute it is
when it's all riled up.

01:01:25.373 --> 01:01:27.820
It's god-dang precious.

01:01:41.721 --> 01:01:43.486
Psst!  Hey, twig!

01:01:43.486 --> 01:01:45.187
Come here.

01:01:45.986 --> 01:01:47.256
Come on.

01:01:53.930 --> 01:01:56.859
Man. What'd they do to you?

01:01:59.694 --> 01:02:02.402
Hey, you want to
help us get out of here?

01:02:03.033 --> 01:02:06.217
There's something I need you
to get and bring back to me.

01:02:06.424 --> 01:02:10.627
In the captain's quarters,
there's a prototype fin.

01:02:11.123 --> 01:02:13.318
The thing I wore in my head.

01:02:13.318 --> 01:02:15.318
There's a drawer next to the bunk.

01:02:15.318 --> 01:02:17.300
It's in that. It's red.

01:02:17.538 --> 01:02:19.343
You got it?

01:02:53.702 --> 01:02:55.436
That's my underwear.

01:02:55.436 --> 01:02:57.723
Yeah, I was pretty sure he didn't
know what you were talking about.

01:02:57.723 --> 01:02:59.789
You have to explain
it more careful.

01:03:01.386 --> 01:03:05.399
It's a prototype fin.

01:03:10.528 --> 01:03:11.999
That's an Orloni.

01:03:11.999 --> 01:03:13.911
It's a fin, Groot.

01:03:13.911 --> 01:03:15.789
You try it this time.

01:03:16.453 --> 01:03:17.708
All right.

01:03:18.842 --> 01:03:21.185
That's Vorker's eye.

01:03:21.185 --> 01:03:23.133
He takes it out when he sleeps.

01:03:23.133 --> 01:03:25.971
- Go, look again.
- But leave the eye here.

01:03:26.732 --> 01:03:29.554
- Why?
- He's gonna wake up tomorrow...

01:03:29.554 --> 01:03:31.457
and he's not gonna know...

01:03:31.457 --> 01:03:33.822
...where his eye is!

01:03:40.687 --> 01:03:42.552
That's a desk.

01:03:42.552 --> 01:03:44.743
We told you it was this big.

01:03:51.542 --> 01:03:54.260
Tell me you guys have
a refrigerator somewhere...

01:03:54.260 --> 01:03:56.712
...with a bunch of
severed human toes.

01:03:56.712 --> 01:04:00.276
Okay, then let's just agree
to never discuss this.

01:04:03.798 --> 01:04:07.919
The drawer you want to open
has this symbol on it.

01:04:07.919 --> 01:04:09.620
Okay?

01:04:18.035 --> 01:04:19.518
What? No!

01:04:19.518 --> 01:04:21.524
He thinks you want him
to wear it as a hat.

01:04:21.524 --> 01:04:22.726
That's not what I said!

01:04:22.726 --> 01:04:25.198
- I am Groot!
- He's relieved you don't want him to.

01:04:25.198 --> 01:04:27.088
- I am Groot.
- He hates hats.

01:04:27.088 --> 01:04:29.178
- I am Groot.
- On anyone, not just himself.

01:04:29.178 --> 01:04:30.979
- I am Groot?
- One minute, you think someone

01:04:30.979 --> 01:04:33.087
has a weird shaped head, the next minute,

01:04:33.087 --> 01:04:34.923
just because, you realize part of that head is the hat.

01:04:35.314 --> 01:04:37.099
That's why you don't like hats?

01:04:37.593 --> 01:04:40.170
This is an important
conversation right now?

01:05:15.032 --> 01:05:16.936
What you have there?

01:05:24.852 --> 01:05:27.220
I didn't mean to do a mutiny.

01:05:29.124 --> 01:05:31.526
They killed all my friends.

01:05:34.606 --> 01:05:37.230
Get the third quadrant
ready for release.

01:05:43.645 --> 01:05:45.014
One more thing.

01:05:45.967 --> 01:05:48.311
You got any clones of
Quill's old music on the ship?

01:06:35.648 --> 01:06:38.164
He's got it!
Yondu got the fin!

01:06:38.164 --> 01:06:39.077
Go!

01:07:17.895 --> 01:07:18.967
Down there!

01:09:15.979 --> 01:09:17.673
You maniac!

01:09:19.642 --> 01:09:21.620
The whole ship's gonna blow.

01:09:32.751 --> 01:09:34.556
Not the whole ship.

01:09:52.935 --> 01:09:55.581
- Who is this?
- I am sending you the

01:09:55.581 --> 01:09:58.498
coordinates for Yondu's ship.

01:09:59.116 --> 01:10:01.201
- Release the quadrant!
- Aye, captain!

01:10:01.201 --> 01:10:04.080
I only ask one thing.

01:10:04.591 --> 01:10:06.532
That your High Priestess...

01:10:06.532 --> 01:10:10.489
...tell him the name of
the man what sealed his fate.

01:10:11.304 --> 01:10:13.710
Taserface.

01:10:38.623 --> 01:10:40.844
- Where to, captain?
- Ego.

01:10:42.819 --> 01:10:44.342
No, boy!

01:10:52.331 --> 01:10:57.492
It ain't healthy, mammalian body
to hop more than 50 jumps at a time.

01:10:57.492 --> 01:11:01.372
- I know that.
- We're about to do 700!

01:11:16.263 --> 01:11:18.393
So, I guess this could all
be mine someday.

01:11:19.941 --> 01:11:22.516
Rocket?
Rocket, are you there?

01:11:30.495 --> 01:11:31.870
What are you doing, Peter?

01:11:34.798 --> 01:11:36.098
Dance with me.

01:11:36.532 --> 01:11:38.319
I'm not going to dance with you.

01:11:38.319 --> 01:11:40.657
This is Sam Cooke...

01:11:40.657 --> 01:11:43.482
...one of the greatest
Earth singers of all time.

01:12:15.452 --> 01:12:17.571
Drax says you're not a dancer.

01:12:18.742 --> 01:12:21.825
If you ever tell anyone about this...

01:12:21.825 --> 01:12:23.128
...I will kill you.

01:12:23.863 --> 01:12:25.388
When are we going to do something

01:12:25.388 --> 01:12:27.498
about this unspoken thing between us?

01:12:28.840 --> 01:12:30.434
What unspoken thing?

01:12:31.953 --> 01:12:33.137
This...

01:12:33.950 --> 01:12:36.535
Cheers, Sam and Diane.

01:12:37.097 --> 01:12:40.276
...guy and a girl on a
TV show who dig each other...

01:12:40.276 --> 01:12:42.746
...but never say it because the
TV ratings would go down...

01:12:42.746 --> 01:12:44.047
...sort of thing.

01:12:44.047 --> 01:12:45.698
There's no unspoken thing here.

01:12:47.893 --> 01:12:50.030
Well, it's a catch-22, because if
you said it then it would be spoken...

01:12:50.030 --> 01:12:52.364
...and you'd be a liar.

01:12:52.364 --> 01:12:54.181
So, by not saying it...

01:12:54.771 --> 01:12:58.268
...you are telling the truth
and admitting that there is.

01:12:59.328 --> 01:13:01.139
No, that's not what I...

01:13:03.915 --> 01:13:08.039
What we should be discussing
right now is, something about this place.

01:13:08.387 --> 01:13:10.239
It doesn't feel right.

01:13:10.727 --> 01:13:12.412
What are you talking about?

01:13:13.371 --> 01:13:15.071
You're the one who
wanted me to come here.

01:13:15.071 --> 01:13:17.362
That girl, Mantis...
...she's afraid of something.

01:13:17.981 --> 01:13:20.243
Why are you trying to take
this away from me?

01:13:20.454 --> 01:13:23.920
- I'm not trying....
- He's my father. He's blood.

01:13:23.920 --> 01:13:25.829
Well you have blood on Earth,
you never wanted to return there.

01:13:25.829 --> 01:13:27.732
Again, you made me come here.

01:13:27.732 --> 01:13:30.354
And Earth, Earth is the place
where my mother died in front of me.

01:13:30.354 --> 01:13:33.827
No, it's because that place is
real, and this is a fantasy.

01:13:33.827 --> 01:13:36.828
This is real!
I'm only half human, remember?

01:13:36.828 --> 01:13:38.206
That's the half I'm worried about.

01:13:38.929 --> 01:13:40.553
I get it.
You're jealous...

01:13:40.553 --> 01:13:43.902
...because I'm part god and
you like when I'm the weak one.

01:13:43.902 --> 01:13:46.289
You were insufferable to begin with.

01:13:46.542 --> 01:13:48.165
I haven't been able
to reach Rocket.

01:13:48.165 --> 01:13:49.765
I'm going to go outside and
try to get a signal.

01:13:49.765 --> 01:13:52.416
You know what?
This is not Cheers after all.

01:13:52.829 --> 01:13:55.586
This is whatever the show is where
one person is willing to...

01:13:55.586 --> 01:13:57.466
...open themselves up to new
possibilities,

01:13:57.466 --> 01:14:00.553
and the other person is a jerk who
doesn't trust anybody!

01:14:00.553 --> 01:14:02.318
It's a show that doesn't exist!

01:14:02.318 --> 01:14:04.219
That's why it would get zero ratings.

01:14:04.219 --> 01:14:06.117
I don't know what Cheers is.

01:14:06.117 --> 01:14:07.772
I finally found my family.

01:14:07.772 --> 01:14:09.408
Don't you understand that?

01:14:10.266 --> 01:14:11.878
I thought you already had.

01:14:38.665 --> 01:14:40.356
Damn it.

01:15:10.475 --> 01:15:11.775
Psychopath!

01:17:10.716 --> 01:17:12.016
Are you kidding me!

01:17:36.986 --> 01:17:38.143
I win.

01:17:38.143 --> 01:17:40.010
I win, I bested you in combat.

01:17:40.010 --> 01:17:41.995
No.
I saved your life.

01:17:41.995 --> 01:17:43.922
Well you were stupid
enough to let me live.

01:17:43.922 --> 01:17:44.749
You let me live!

01:17:44.749 --> 01:17:46.552
I don't need you to
always try and defeat me!

01:17:46.552 --> 01:17:49.240
I'm not the one who just flew across the
universe just because I wanted to win.

01:17:49.240 --> 01:17:50.991
Do not tell me what I want.

01:17:50.991 --> 01:17:53.189
I don't need to tell you
what you want! It's obvious!

01:17:53.189 --> 01:17:56.666
You were the one who wanted to win.
And I just wanted a sister!

01:18:03.223 --> 01:18:04.890
You were all I had.

01:18:05.915 --> 01:18:08.133
But you were the one
who needed to win.

01:18:09.610 --> 01:18:11.965
Thanos pulled my eye
from my head...

01:18:12.359 --> 01:18:14.081
...and my brain from my skull...

01:18:15.300 --> 01:18:17.191
...and my arm from my body...

01:18:18.719 --> 01:18:20.525
...because of you.

01:18:43.993 --> 01:18:45.293
You all right, son?

01:18:48.679 --> 01:18:52.367
I saw your girl stomp off
a little earlier in quite a huff.

01:18:52.367 --> 01:18:53.741
Yeah.

01:18:53.741 --> 01:18:57.117
It's fortuitous, you listening to this song.

01:18:57.707 --> 01:18:59.948
You know, uh, "Brandy?"

01:18:59.948 --> 01:19:01.660
By Looking Glass?

01:19:03.051 --> 01:19:05.220
A favorite of your mom's.

01:19:05.502 --> 01:19:06.802
Yes.  Yeah, it was.

01:19:07.199 --> 01:19:09.891
One of Earth's greatest
musical compositions.

01:19:09.891 --> 01:19:13.384
- Perhaps its very greatest.
- Yeah, yes!

01:19:13.384 --> 01:19:17.422
You know, Peter, you and I, we're...
we're the sailor in that song.

01:19:19.229 --> 01:19:21.183
He came on a summer's day.

01:19:21.792 --> 01:19:24.907
Bringing gifts from far away.

01:19:25.502 --> 01:19:29.326
Like the child I put
in your mother.

01:19:29.326 --> 01:19:31.952
Or the freedom you brought Gamora.

01:19:34.365 --> 01:19:37.664
Brandy, you're a fine girl.

01:19:37.664 --> 01:19:40.380
What a good wife you would be.

01:19:41.906 --> 01:19:44.836
My life, my love,

01:19:44.836 --> 01:19:48.372
my lady, is the sea.

01:19:48.828 --> 01:19:50.968
The sea calls the sailor back.

01:19:50.968 --> 01:19:54.464
And he loves the girl, but
that's not his place.

01:19:54.740 --> 01:19:58.265
The sea calls upon him as
history

01:19:58.265 --> 01:19:59.569
calls upon great men.

01:20:00.316 --> 01:20:04.273
And sometimes we are deprived
the pleasures of mortals.

01:20:04.904 --> 01:20:07.511
Well, you may not be
mortal, but me...

01:20:07.511 --> 01:20:11.239
No, Peter. Death will remain a
stranger to both of us,

01:20:11.239 --> 01:20:13.998
...as long as the light
burns in this planet.

01:20:14.692 --> 01:20:16.181
I'm immortal?

01:20:18.562 --> 01:20:20.574
- Really?
- Yes!

01:20:20.978 --> 01:20:23.214
As long as this light exists.

01:20:23.901 --> 01:20:25.958
And I can use the light to

01:20:25.958 --> 01:20:28.052
build cool things, like...

01:20:28.268 --> 01:20:29.780
...how you made this whole planet?

01:20:29.780 --> 01:20:32.856
Well, it may take you a few
million years of practice...

01:20:32.856 --> 01:20:35.549
...before you get
really good at it. But, yes!

01:20:36.292 --> 01:20:40.108
This is...!  Well, get ready for
an 800-foot

01:20:40.108 --> 01:20:42.624
statue of Pac-Man, with Skeletor and Heather Locklear.

01:20:42.977 --> 01:20:45.562
- Whatever you want.
- I'm gonna make some weird shit.

01:20:45.562 --> 01:20:48.970
You know, Peter, it is
a tremendous responsibility.

01:20:49.217 --> 01:20:52.088
Only we can remake the universe.

01:20:52.088 --> 01:20:55.428
Only we can take the
bridle of the cosmos...

01:20:55.428 --> 01:20:57.630
...and lead it to
where it needs to go.

01:20:59.577 --> 01:21:00.635
How?

01:21:12.270 --> 01:21:13.771
Come with me.

01:21:24.703 --> 01:21:26.745
Drax.
Drax. Drax.

01:21:26.745 --> 01:21:28.997
Drax.
We need to talk.

01:21:31.109 --> 01:21:35.419
I'm sorry. But I like a woman with
some meat on her bones.

01:21:35.731 --> 01:21:38.107
- What?
- I tried to let you down easily by

01:21:38.107 --> 01:21:42.606
- telling you I found you disgusting.
- No, that's not why...

01:21:46.409 --> 01:21:47.974
What are you doing?

01:21:48.667 --> 01:21:51.310
I'm imagining being with you.

01:21:51.310 --> 01:21:54.318
Drax, that's not...
I don't like you like that.

01:21:54.600 --> 01:21:57.134
I don't even know the
type of thing you are.

01:21:57.134 --> 01:21:59.950
Hey!
There's no need to get personal.

01:21:59.950 --> 01:22:03.355
Listen!
Ego's gotten exactly what he wanted.

01:22:03.355 --> 01:22:06.313
I should have told you earlier.
I is stupid.

01:22:07.328 --> 01:22:08.946
You are in danger.

01:22:15.590 --> 01:22:17.129
What is that?

01:22:19.667 --> 01:22:24.291
Now, you need to readjust
the way you process life.

01:22:24.291 --> 01:22:27.695
Everything around us,
including the girl...

01:22:27.695 --> 01:22:31.501
...everything is temporary.

01:22:31.932 --> 01:22:34.785
We are forever.

01:22:35.286 --> 01:22:36.786
Doesn't eternity get boring?

01:22:36.786 --> 01:22:38.970
Not if you have a purpose, Peter.

01:22:38.970 --> 01:22:41.407
Which is why you're here.

01:22:42.013 --> 01:22:44.462
I told you how all those years ago...

01:22:44.462 --> 01:22:48.698
...I had an unceasing
impulse to find life.

01:22:49.364 --> 01:22:53.718
But what I did not tell you
is how I finally did find it.

01:22:54.806 --> 01:22:56.988
It was all so...

01:22:58.730 --> 01:23:00.280
...disappointing.

01:23:00.990 --> 01:23:03.938
And that is when I came...

01:23:04.913 --> 01:23:09.448
...to a profound realization.

01:23:10.417 --> 01:23:15.084
My innate desire to
seek out other life...

01:23:15.697 --> 01:23:20.530
...was not so that I
could walk among that life.

01:23:22.920 --> 01:23:24.419
Peter.

01:23:25.035 --> 01:23:28.386
I have found meaning.

01:23:47.063 --> 01:23:49.508
I see it.

01:23:50.766 --> 01:23:52.645
Eternity.

01:23:53.165 --> 01:23:55.011
Oh, my God.

01:24:04.511 --> 01:24:06.552
We need to get off this planet.

01:24:19.822 --> 01:24:23.616
Anyway, before I was so
rudely interrupted.

01:24:23.616 --> 01:24:26.930
At that time, I was
a Federal Express man.

01:24:36.532 --> 01:24:38.659
What the hell you doing, boy?

01:24:38.659 --> 01:24:42.055
I could tell by how you talked about him,
this Ego is bad news.

01:24:42.055 --> 01:24:43.643
We are here to save Quill.

01:24:43.643 --> 01:24:48.040
For what?  Huh?
For honor? For love?

01:24:48.040 --> 01:24:50.418
No.
I don't care about those things.

01:24:50.418 --> 01:24:53.271
I want to save Quill so I
can prove I'm better than him!

01:24:53.271 --> 01:24:56.125
I can lord this
over him forever.

01:24:57.606 --> 01:24:58.968
What are you laughing
at me for?

01:24:59.838 --> 01:25:03.815
Oh, you can fool yourself and
everyone else, but you can't fool me.

01:25:04.402 --> 01:25:05.815
I know who you are.

01:25:05.815 --> 01:25:08.120
You do not know anything
about me, loser.

01:25:08.120 --> 01:25:10.325
I know everything about you.

01:25:10.697 --> 01:25:13.327
I know you play like you're the
meanest and the hardest...

01:25:13.327 --> 01:25:15.695
- ...but actually you're the most scared of all.
- Shut up!

01:25:15.695 --> 01:25:17.857
I know you steal batteries
you don't need...

01:25:17.857 --> 01:25:20.304
...and you push away anyone
who's willing to put up with you...

01:25:20.304 --> 01:25:21.920
Because just a little bit of love...

01:25:21.920 --> 01:25:25.425
...reminds you how big and empty
that hole inside you actually is.

01:25:25.425 --> 01:25:28.301
- I said, shut up!
- I know them scientists that made

01:25:28.301 --> 01:25:31.187
- you never gave a rat's ass about you.
- I'm serious, dude.

01:25:31.187 --> 01:25:34.574
Just like my own damn parents,
who sold me...

01:25:34.574 --> 01:25:36.716
... their own little
baby, into slavery.

01:25:36.716 --> 01:25:39.138
I know who you are, boy.

01:25:39.138 --> 01:25:41.416
Because you're me.

01:25:47.081 --> 01:25:49.381
What kind of a pair are we.

01:25:50.308 --> 01:25:53.409
The kinds that's about to
go fight a planet, I reckon.

01:25:53.409 --> 01:25:55.571
All right!
Okay.

01:25:55.571 --> 01:25:56.410
Wait.

01:25:56.982 --> 01:25:57.996
Fight a what?

01:26:01.826 --> 01:26:04.143
Who are you people?
What is this place?

01:26:04.143 --> 01:26:05.722
Gamora, let her go!

01:26:05.722 --> 01:26:07.880
The bodies in the
caverns, who are they?

01:26:07.880 --> 01:26:10.149
You are scared.

01:26:12.691 --> 01:26:15.974
I call it, the Expansion.

01:26:16.796 --> 01:26:18.809
It is my purpose.

01:26:18.809 --> 01:26:20.402
Now,

01:26:20.402 --> 01:26:24.134
it is yours, as well.

01:26:24.503 --> 01:26:26.330
It's beautiful.

01:26:27.153 --> 01:26:29.015
Over thousands of years...

01:26:29.015 --> 01:26:32.558
...I implanted thousands
of extension of myself...

01:26:32.558 --> 01:26:35.130
...on thousands of worlds.

01:26:35.130 --> 01:26:39.059
I need to fulfill life's
one true purpose...

01:26:39.059 --> 01:26:40.766
...to grow and spread...

01:26:40.766 --> 01:26:44.055
...covering all that exists...

01:26:44.055 --> 01:26:48.474
...until everything is...

01:26:49.198 --> 01:26:50.498
Me.

01:26:50.974 --> 01:26:52.816
What did she do to me?

01:26:53.106 --> 01:26:55.012
She already told me everything.

01:26:55.012 --> 01:26:57.562
I only had one problem.

01:26:58.082 --> 01:27:02.639
A single Celestial doesn't have
enough power for such an enterprise.

01:27:03.174 --> 01:27:06.342
But two Celestials...
Well, now...

01:27:06.342 --> 01:27:08.985
that just might do.

01:27:11.089 --> 01:27:14.883
The bodies...
are his children.

01:27:15.818 --> 01:27:17.439
Out of all my labors...

01:27:17.439 --> 01:27:20.784
...the most beguiling
was attempting to...

01:27:20.784 --> 01:27:22.684
...graft my DNA with
that of another species.

01:27:22.684 --> 01:27:25.755
I hoped the result of such
a coupling would be...

01:27:25.755 --> 01:27:27.938
...enough to power the Expansion.

01:27:28.313 --> 01:27:30.962
I had Yondu deliver
some of them to me.

01:27:31.165 --> 01:27:33.509
It broke the Ravager code, but

01:27:33.509 --> 01:27:36.211
I compensated him generously, and...

01:27:36.211 --> 01:27:39.167
...to ease his conscience,
I said I'd never hurt them.

01:27:39.167 --> 01:27:41.716
And that was true,
they never felt a thing.

01:27:41.716 --> 01:27:44.963
But, one after the
other, they failed me.

01:27:45.682 --> 01:27:49.011
Not one of them
carried the Celestial genes.

01:27:49.888 --> 01:27:51.713
Until you, Peter.

01:27:52.501 --> 01:27:54.719
Out of all my spawn...

01:27:55.537 --> 01:27:59.515
...only you carry the
connection to the light.

01:27:59.864 --> 01:28:03.101
We need to find Peter now
and get off this damn planet.

01:28:03.101 --> 01:28:06.795
Ego will have brought
him to his side by now.

01:28:06.795 --> 01:28:09.675
- Then we just go.
- No! He's our friend.

01:28:09.675 --> 01:28:12.197
All any of you do is yell at each other.

01:28:12.197 --> 01:28:14.634
- You're not friends.
- You're right.

01:28:15.868 --> 01:28:17.464
We're family.

01:28:18.709 --> 01:28:20.845
We leave no one behind.

01:28:23.953 --> 01:28:25.320
Except maybe you.

01:28:27.433 --> 01:28:29.978
For the first time
in my existence...

01:28:30.644 --> 01:28:33.784
...I am truly not alone!

01:28:39.713 --> 01:28:41.670
What is it, son?

01:28:44.375 --> 01:28:45.999
My friends.

01:28:46.488 --> 01:28:51.135
Oh, no, you see,
that's the mortal in you, Peter.

01:28:52.052 --> 01:28:55.838
We are beyond such things.

01:28:55.838 --> 01:28:57.276
Yes.

01:28:59.859 --> 01:29:01.866
- Now...
- But my mother...

01:29:04.225 --> 01:29:06.679
You said you loved my mother.

01:29:06.679 --> 01:29:08.519
And that I did.

01:29:09.584 --> 01:29:11.861
My River Lily who knew all the words

01:29:11.861 --> 01:29:14.749
to every song that came over the radio.

01:29:16.607 --> 01:29:19.713
I returned to Earth to
see her three times.

01:29:19.713 --> 01:29:22.593
And I knew if I returned a 4th...

01:29:22.593 --> 01:29:24.404
...I'd never leave.

01:29:25.278 --> 01:29:26.975
The Expansion...

01:29:28.635 --> 01:29:30.990
...the reason for my very
existence would be over, so...

01:29:30.990 --> 01:29:33.136
...I did what I had to do.

01:29:33.563 --> 01:29:34.963
But...

01:29:36.227 --> 01:29:39.938
it broke my heart
to put that tumor in her head.

01:29:44.825 --> 01:29:46.125
What?

01:29:46.125 --> 01:29:49.533
Now, now, I know
that sounds bad.

01:30:01.896 --> 01:30:05.590
Who in the hell
do you think you are?

01:30:05.590 --> 01:30:10.506
- You killed my mother!
- I tried so hard...

01:30:11.032 --> 01:30:15.136
...to find the form that best suited you...

01:30:15.531 --> 01:30:18.508
...and this is
the thanks I get?

01:30:18.508 --> 01:30:22.427
You really need to grow up!

01:30:26.424 --> 01:30:28.805
I wanted to do this together,

01:30:28.805 --> 01:30:32.947
but I suppose you'll have to learn
by spending the next 1000 years

01:30:32.947 --> 01:30:34.550
as a battery!

01:30:35.993 --> 01:30:38.516
Finally.
Rocket?

01:30:38.516 --> 01:30:41.345
Keep that transmitter
nearby so I can find you.

01:30:41.345 --> 01:30:43.590
We're in an old piece of construction
Wip and Yondu once used

01:30:43.590 --> 01:30:46.729
to slice open the bank of A'askavaria.

01:30:46.729 --> 01:30:49.071
- Ego's unhinged.
- I know. Get ready.

01:30:49.071 --> 01:30:50.915
Drop it, Kraglin.

01:31:10.358 --> 01:31:11.736
No.

01:31:23.254 --> 01:31:26.400
My life, my love,

01:31:26.681 --> 01:31:29.613
my lady is the sea.

01:31:31.122 --> 01:31:32.379
Peter.

01:31:32.999 --> 01:31:35.967
This is the sea.

01:32:16.508 --> 01:32:18.880
Hey there, jackass!

01:32:27.202 --> 01:32:30.007
What is that thing?

01:32:35.611 --> 01:32:38.281
Out of the way,
dumber, smaller Groot!

01:32:42.069 --> 01:32:44.209
I told you something
didn't feel right.

01:32:44.209 --> 01:32:46.784
I told you so? It's just what
I hate to hear right now.

01:32:46.784 --> 01:32:50.134
- I came back, didn't I?
- Because of our unspoken thing.

01:32:50.134 --> 01:32:52.035
There's no unspoken thing.

01:32:52.035 --> 01:32:54.159
What are you doing?
You could've killed us all.

01:32:54.159 --> 01:32:56.987
- "Ahn... Thank you, Rocket"?
- We had it under control.

01:32:56.987 --> 01:33:00.245
We did not. That is only an
extension of his true self.

01:33:00.245 --> 01:33:01.345
He'll be back soon.

01:33:01.345 --> 01:33:04.342
- What's Smurfette doing here?
- Whatever I need to get a damn ride home.

01:33:04.342 --> 01:33:07.634
- She tried to murder me!
- I saved you, you stupid fox!

01:33:07.634 --> 01:33:09.761
- He's not a fox.
- I am Groot.

01:33:09.761 --> 01:33:11.894
- I'm not a "rabboon" either.
- I am Groot.

01:33:11.894 --> 01:33:13.727
Raccoon. Whatever.

01:33:16.570 --> 01:33:19.309
- How do we kill a Celestial?
- There's a center to him.

01:33:19.309 --> 01:33:22.947
His brain, his soul, whatever it is,
in some sort of protective shell.

01:33:22.947 --> 01:33:25.528
It's in the caverns
below the surface.

01:33:27.176 --> 01:33:28.576
Yondu?

01:33:36.563 --> 01:33:38.064
Thrusters are out.

01:33:38.064 --> 01:33:39.906
Guess I should be
glad I was a skinny kid,

01:33:39.906 --> 01:33:41.731
otherwise you woulda
delivered me to this maniac.

01:33:41.731 --> 01:33:44.021
You still reckon that's the reason
I kept you around, you idiot?

01:33:44.021 --> 01:33:45.928
That's what you told
me, you old doofus.

01:33:45.928 --> 01:33:48.556
Well once I figured out what
happened to them other kids...

01:33:48.556 --> 01:33:51.200
- I wasn't gonna hand you over.
- You said you were gonna eat me.

01:33:51.745 --> 01:33:54.311
- That was being funny!
- Not to me!

01:33:54.311 --> 01:33:55.875
You people have issues.

01:33:55.875 --> 01:33:58.173
Well of course I have issues.

01:33:58.173 --> 01:34:00.226
That's my freaking father!

01:34:00.779 --> 01:34:02.545
Thrusters are back up.

01:34:14.481 --> 01:34:16.726
- We should be going up!
- We can't.

01:34:16.726 --> 01:34:19.264
Ego wants to eradicate
the universe as we know it.

01:34:19.264 --> 01:34:20.451
We have to kill him.

01:34:20.451 --> 01:34:22.339
- Rocket!
- Yup!

01:34:34.838 --> 01:34:36.575
So we're saving the galaxy again?

01:34:36.575 --> 01:34:39.397
- I guess.
- Awesome!

01:34:40.882 --> 01:34:42.953
We're really gonna be
able to jack up our price

01:34:42.953 --> 01:34:44.842
if we're 2-time galaxy saving.

01:34:44.842 --> 01:34:46.800
I seriously can't believe
that's where your mind goes.

01:34:46.800 --> 01:34:49.473
It was just a random thought,
man. I thought we were friends?

01:34:49.473 --> 01:34:51.822
Of course, I care about
the planets and the buildings...

01:34:51.822 --> 01:34:53.563
and all the animals
and the planets.

01:34:53.563 --> 01:34:54.769
And the people.

01:34:54.769 --> 01:34:59.548
The crabby puppy's so cute.
He makes me want to die!

01:35:11.371 --> 01:35:13.227
Soup! Soup!

01:35:34.377 --> 01:35:36.906
Pilots, release envoy units.

01:35:38.594 --> 01:35:42.636
Our sensors detect a battery
below the surface of the planet.

01:35:43.841 --> 01:35:45.241
Dive!

01:36:01.243 --> 01:36:02.643
Cap'n?

01:36:02.643 --> 01:36:03.944
Cap'n?

01:36:08.252 --> 01:36:10.299
Tell me, why did Ego
want you here?

01:36:10.299 --> 01:36:12.220
He needs my genetic
connection

01:36:12.220 --> 01:36:13.969
to the light to help
destroy the universe.

01:36:13.969 --> 01:36:16.133
He tried to teach me how
to control the power.

01:36:16.133 --> 01:36:18.610
- So could you?
- A little.

01:36:18.610 --> 01:36:21.188
- I made a ball.
- A ball?

01:36:21.188 --> 01:36:22.838
I thought as hard as I could.

01:36:22.838 --> 01:36:25.109
- It was all that I can come up with.
- You thought?

01:36:25.109 --> 01:36:27.070
You think when I
make this arrow fly,

01:36:27.070 --> 01:36:28.571
that I use my head?

01:36:52.535 --> 01:36:55.639
There. That's Ego's core.

01:36:58.171 --> 01:37:01.881
- That core is thick, Rocket.
- I got it covered.

01:37:08.789 --> 01:37:10.189
We must hurry.

01:37:10.189 --> 01:37:13.155
It will not take
Ego long to find us.

01:37:17.756 --> 01:37:19.501
Keep it steady.

01:37:26.213 --> 01:37:29.052
We draw him to the
center then we kill him.

01:37:36.529 --> 01:37:39.617
- Cap'n?
- What is it, Kraglin?

01:37:39.617 --> 01:37:43.102
- Hey, remember that Ayesha chick?
- Yeah, why?

01:37:43.102 --> 01:37:45.474
Oh, hell!

01:38:08.436 --> 01:38:10.512
Why aren't you firing the lasers?

01:38:10.512 --> 01:38:12.587
They blew up the generator.

01:38:12.587 --> 01:38:15.387
I think I packed a
small detonator.

01:38:15.387 --> 01:38:17.836
A detonator is worthless
without explosives.

01:38:17.836 --> 01:38:19.887
Well, we got these.

01:38:20.475 --> 01:38:22.592
Is that thing strong
enough to kill Ego?

01:38:22.592 --> 01:38:26.536
If it is, it will cause a chain reaction
throughout his entire nervous system.

01:38:26.799 --> 01:38:30.176
- Meaning what?
- The entire planet will explode.

01:38:30.176 --> 01:38:32.184
We'll have to get
out of here, fast.

01:38:32.403 --> 01:38:34.246
I rigged the timer.

01:38:34.825 --> 01:38:36.225
Go!

01:38:51.798 --> 01:38:53.516
He's coming!

01:38:55.446 --> 01:38:57.719
Didn't you say you can
make him sleep?

01:38:57.719 --> 01:39:00.657
When he wants.
He's too powerful!

01:39:00.657 --> 01:39:02.112
I can't!

01:39:02.766 --> 01:39:04.875
You will have to
believe in yourself.

01:39:04.875 --> 01:39:08.007
Because I believe in you.

01:39:21.460 --> 01:39:23.180
Sleep!

01:39:30.585 --> 01:39:32.613
I never thought she'd
be able to do it...

01:39:32.613 --> 01:39:35.169
with as weak and skinny
as she appears to be.

01:39:36.257 --> 01:39:39.300
I don't know how
long I can hold him!

01:39:43.156 --> 01:39:44.764
The metal's too thick.

01:39:44.764 --> 01:39:48.936
For the bomb to work, we actually
need to place it on Ego's core.

01:39:49.343 --> 01:39:52.235
And our fat butts ain't gonna fit
through those tiny holes.

01:39:52.587 --> 01:39:54.192
Well...

01:39:56.480 --> 01:39:58.341
That's a terrible idea.

01:39:58.341 --> 01:40:01.352
Which is the only kind of
idea we have left.

01:40:02.254 --> 01:40:03.809
Unbelievable.

01:40:03.809 --> 01:40:07.313
"Rocket, do this.",
"Rocket, do that."

01:40:08.482 --> 01:40:09.999
What a day.

01:40:18.489 --> 01:40:22.121
All right. First, you flip this
switch, then this switch.

01:40:22.121 --> 01:40:23.754
That activates it.

01:40:24.028 --> 01:40:26.325
Then you push this button.

01:40:26.325 --> 01:40:29.375
Which will give you five
minutes to get out of there.

01:40:30.028 --> 01:40:31.995
Now, whatever you do...

01:40:31.995 --> 01:40:34.437
Don't push this button.

01:40:34.703 --> 01:40:38.873
Because that would set off the bomb
immediately and we'll all be dead.

01:40:38.873 --> 01:40:41.755
Now, repeat back
what I just said.

01:40:42.187 --> 01:40:43.943
I am Groot.

01:40:44.155 --> 01:40:46.327
- I am Groot.
- That's right.

01:40:46.531 --> 01:40:48.086
- I am Groot.
- No!

01:40:48.367 --> 01:40:51.045
No, that's the button
that will kill everyone!

01:40:51.414 --> 01:40:52.853
Try again.

01:40:55.476 --> 01:40:57.210
I am Groot.

01:40:57.210 --> 01:40:59.108
I am Groot.

01:40:59.686 --> 01:41:02.171
- I am Groot.
- No! That's exactly what you just said,

01:41:02.171 --> 01:41:03.913
how is that even possible?

01:41:03.913 --> 01:41:07.232
Which button is the button
you're supposed to push? Point to it.

01:41:07.680 --> 01:41:08.560
No!

01:41:08.560 --> 01:41:10.459
Hey, you're making him nervous!

01:41:10.459 --> 01:41:12.287
Shut up and
give me some tape!

01:41:12.287 --> 01:41:15.221
Does anybody have any tape out there?
I wanna put some tape over the death button.

01:41:15.221 --> 01:41:17.716
I don't have any tape.
Let me check.

01:41:18.421 --> 01:41:19.564
<i>Yo, Yondu!</i>

01:41:19.564 --> 01:41:23.548
...do you have any...ouch!
Do you have any tape?

01:41:25.161 --> 01:41:27.744
Gamora?
You have the tape?

01:41:28.157 --> 01:41:29.244
<i>Tape!</i>

01:41:29.244 --> 01:41:30.775
<i>Ah, never mind.</i>

01:41:32.408 --> 01:41:35.140
Drax?
Do you have any tape?

01:41:35.511 --> 01:41:37.878
Yeah, Scotch tape would work.

01:41:37.878 --> 01:41:41.719
Then why did you ask me
if Scotch tape would work
if you don't have any?

01:41:42.095 --> 01:41:43.392
Nobody has any tape!

01:41:43.392 --> 01:41:45.861
- Not a single person has tape?
- Nope.

01:41:45.861 --> 01:41:48.846
- Did you ask Nebula?
- Yes!

01:41:48.846 --> 01:41:50.153
Are you sure?

01:41:50.153 --> 01:41:52.713
I asked Yondu and she was
sitting right next to him.

01:41:52.713 --> 01:41:54.035
I knew you're lying!

01:41:54.035 --> 01:41:56.603
You have priceless batteries and
an atomic bomb in your bag.

01:41:56.603 --> 01:41:58.744
If anybody's gonna
have tape, it's you!

01:41:58.744 --> 01:42:01.978
That's exactly my point!
I have to do everything!

01:42:01.978 --> 01:42:04.279
You are wasting
a lot of time here!

01:42:10.307 --> 01:42:12.285
We're all gonna die.

01:42:13.651 --> 01:42:15.971
Ah, rear thrusters are out again!

01:42:15.971 --> 01:42:18.409
We're done for
without that generator!

01:42:30.971 --> 01:42:32.799
<i>Guardians.</i>

01:42:32.799 --> 01:42:34.768
<i>Perhaps it will provide you solace...</i>

01:42:34.768 --> 01:42:37.541
...that your deaths
are not without purpose.

01:42:37.541 --> 01:42:41.721
They will serve as a warning for all
of those tempted to betray us.

01:42:41.982 --> 01:42:44.971
Don't screw with the Sovereign.

01:42:48.203 --> 01:42:49.521
This is gonna hurt.

01:42:49.521 --> 01:42:51.529
Promises, promises.

01:43:12.276 --> 01:43:13.711
No!

01:43:13.711 --> 01:43:17.791
No! No! Noooo!

01:43:20.802 --> 01:43:22.620
We're gonna blow!

01:43:27.210 --> 01:43:29.926
Peter!
No!

01:43:47.648 --> 01:43:49.042
What?

01:43:49.042 --> 01:43:51.190
You look like
Mary Poppins.

01:43:51.190 --> 01:43:52.724
Is he cool?

01:43:53.844 --> 01:43:55.909
Hell yeah, he's cool.

01:43:55.909 --> 01:43:58.689
I'm Mary Poppins, y'all!

01:44:23.833 --> 01:44:25.876
Mantis!
Look out!

01:44:37.148 --> 01:44:39.053
She's just unconscious.

01:44:55.502 --> 01:44:57.229
How long 'til the
bomb goes off?

01:44:57.229 --> 01:45:00.002
In the unlikely event
that Groot doesn't kill us all...

01:45:00.002 --> 01:45:01.626
about 6 minutes.

01:45:06.510 --> 01:45:09.267
Kraglin, we need the
quadrant for an extraction.

01:45:09.267 --> 01:45:11.526
- T-minus 5 minutes.
- Aye, cap'n.

01:45:15.637 --> 01:45:18.996
Somebody's gotta be on
top when Kraglin arrives.

01:45:19.407 --> 01:45:21.586
Drax, take Mantis.

01:45:23.357 --> 01:45:25.086
Ow! My nipples!

01:45:33.820 --> 01:45:35.496
Gamora!

01:45:39.225 --> 01:45:40.963
Peter!

01:46:08.351 --> 01:46:09.981
Get over it.

01:46:09.981 --> 01:46:13.723
Come now, Peter.
I know this isn't what you want.

01:46:16.540 --> 01:46:21.288
What kind of father would I be
to let you make this choice?

01:46:55.291 --> 01:46:59.621
Soon, Peter,
we will be all there is.

01:46:59.621 --> 01:47:02.821
So stop pissing me off!

01:47:24.339 --> 01:47:26.697
We have to get up
to the extraction point.

01:47:34.526 --> 01:47:35.826
Go!

01:49:42.611 --> 01:49:43.986
I told you.

01:49:44.722 --> 01:49:48.312
...I don't want
to do this alone.

01:49:51.919 --> 01:49:54.474
You can not deny...

01:49:54.474 --> 01:49:57.762
...the purpose the
universe has bestowed upon you.

01:50:05.542 --> 01:50:08.180
Everyone, I need you
to stay back, it's not safe...

01:50:08.180 --> 01:50:09.498
What is that?

01:50:22.985 --> 01:50:25.585
It doesn't need to
be like this, Peter.

01:50:26.672 --> 01:50:29.916
Why are you destroying
our chance?

01:50:32.240 --> 01:50:35.572
Stop pretending you
aren't what you are.

01:50:37.111 --> 01:50:38.739
One in billions.

01:50:39.425 --> 01:50:41.665
Trillions. Even more.

01:50:43.459 --> 01:50:48.343
What greater meaning
can a life possibly have to offer?

01:50:49.901 --> 01:50:54.215
I don't use my head
to fly the arrows, boy!

01:50:54.215 --> 01:50:56.413
I use my heart...

01:51:28.575 --> 01:51:32.349
You shouldn't have killed my
mom and squished my Walkman.

01:52:09.157 --> 01:52:12.179
Groot! Groot, if you can
hear me, hurry up!

01:52:12.179 --> 01:52:15.512
I'm not sure how long
Quill can keep him distracted!

01:52:15.512 --> 01:52:17.070
<i>Groot! Hurry!</i>

01:53:08.509 --> 01:53:10.947
Yondu, we're about to blow!

01:53:10.947 --> 01:53:13.493
- Get to the ship!
- Not without Quill!

01:53:13.493 --> 01:53:15.803
You need to take care of the twig!

01:53:16.266 --> 01:53:18.082
Not without you.

01:53:19.037 --> 01:53:22.580
I ain't done nothing right
my whole damn life, rat.

01:53:25.087 --> 01:53:26.862
You need to give me this.

01:53:36.852 --> 01:53:39.292
A spacesuit and an aero-rig.

01:53:39.292 --> 01:53:41.025
I only have one of each.

01:53:48.887 --> 01:53:50.243
I...

01:53:52.545 --> 01:53:54.602
I am Groot!

01:53:54.811 --> 01:53:56.454
What's that?

01:53:57.368 --> 01:53:58.329
He says,

01:53:58.329 --> 01:54:01.853
"Welcome to the freaking
Guardians of the Galaxy".

01:54:01.853 --> 01:54:04.624
Only he didn't use "freaking".

01:54:09.868 --> 01:54:11.168
Bye, twig.

01:54:12.535 --> 01:54:15.485
We're gonna have to have a real
discussion about your language.

01:55:15.131 --> 01:55:16.483
Where's Peter?

01:55:17.022 --> 01:55:18.678
Rocket, where is he?

01:55:19.944 --> 01:55:21.244
Rocket?

01:55:21.244 --> 01:55:23.389
Rocket, look at me!
Where is he?

01:55:29.737 --> 01:55:32.369
No, I'm not
leaving without him.

01:55:40.075 --> 01:55:41.375
I'm sorry.

01:55:41.977 --> 01:55:44.593
I can only afford to
lose one friend today.

01:55:45.872 --> 01:55:47.613
Kraglin, go!

01:55:47.613 --> 01:55:49.013
Wait.

01:55:49.492 --> 01:55:50.792
Let's hold back.

01:55:52.959 --> 01:55:54.975
Rocket, where's Quill?

01:55:56.692 --> 01:55:59.758
Rocket, where's Quill?

01:56:01.446 --> 01:56:02.746
<i>Rocket!</i>

01:56:04.358 --> 01:56:06.094
Where's Quill?

01:56:07.453 --> 01:56:09.075
Where's Quill?

01:56:18.558 --> 01:56:21.835
No, we need to stop it.
We need to stop it.

01:56:27.794 --> 01:56:29.986
Stop, listen!
Listen to me.

01:56:30.650 --> 01:56:32.349
You are a god.

01:56:33.364 --> 01:56:34.904
If you kill me...

01:56:35.258 --> 01:56:37.773
...you'll be just
like everybody else.

01:56:39.294 --> 01:56:41.912
What's wrong with that?

01:56:41.912 --> 01:56:43.459
No!

01:57:37.379 --> 01:57:41.290
He may have been your father,
boy, but he wasn't your daddy.

01:57:46.301 --> 01:57:48.937
I'm sorry I didn't
do none of it right.

01:57:49.840 --> 01:57:52.435
Damn lucky you my boy.

01:57:56.450 --> 01:57:57.750
What?

01:58:10.732 --> 01:58:13.441
Yondu, what are you doing?
You can't.

01:58:15.127 --> 01:58:16.427
Yondu!

01:58:21.765 --> 01:58:23.223
No.

01:58:23.223 --> 01:58:24.902
No!

01:58:27.627 --> 01:58:28.627
No!

01:58:31.623 --> 01:58:34.202
No! No!

01:58:35.038 --> 01:58:37.038
Oh! No!

01:59:29.884 --> 01:59:32.639
I told Gamora

01:59:32.639 --> 01:59:35.865
...how when I was a kid, I used to
pretend David Hasselhoff was my dad.

01:59:37.375 --> 01:59:40.348
He is a singer and actor
from Earth, really famous guy.

01:59:42.212 --> 01:59:43.712
Earlier, it struck me...

01:59:44.866 --> 01:59:46.934
...Yondu didn't have a talking car

01:59:46.934 --> 01:59:49.246
but he did have a flying arrow.

01:59:49.695 --> 01:59:51.864
He didn't have the beautiful
voice of an angel...

01:59:51.864 --> 01:59:53.973
...but he did have
the whistle of one.

01:59:54.259 --> 01:59:57.978
Both Yondu and David Hasselhoff
went on kick-ass adventures...

01:59:57.978 --> 01:59:59.809
...and hooked up with hot women...

02:00:00.493 --> 02:00:02.145
...and fought robots.

02:00:05.012 --> 02:00:08.514
I guess David Hasselhoff did kind
of end up being my dad after all.

02:00:09.302 --> 02:00:11.015
Only, it was you, Yondu.

02:00:16.535 --> 02:00:18.558
I had a pretty cool dad.

02:00:21.229 --> 02:00:23.050
What I'm trying to say here is...

02:00:24.760 --> 02:00:29.839
...sometimes the thing you're
searching for your whole life...

02:00:31.563 --> 02:00:33.953
...it's right there
by your side all along.

02:00:33.953 --> 02:00:35.916
You don't even know it.

02:00:47.473 --> 02:00:48.873
I am Groot.

02:00:50.286 --> 02:00:52.073
He did call you twig.

02:00:54.328 --> 02:00:55.628
Nebula.

02:01:00.422 --> 02:01:02.268
I was a child like you.

02:01:03.189 --> 02:01:07.325
I was concerned with staying
alive until the next day, every day.

02:01:07.325 --> 02:01:10.151
And I never considered what
Thanos was doing to you.

02:01:10.402 --> 02:01:12.136
I'm trying to make it right.

02:01:12.355 --> 02:01:16.912
There are little girls like you across
the universe who are in danger.

02:01:18.767 --> 02:01:20.716
You can stay with
us and help them.

02:01:21.163 --> 02:01:23.531
I will help them
by killing Thanos.

02:01:23.531 --> 02:01:25.634
I don't know if
that's possible.

02:01:40.151 --> 02:01:42.304
You will always be my sister.

02:02:25.479 --> 02:02:26.779
<i>Pete!</i>

02:02:29.877 --> 02:02:33.921
The captain found this for you in a junker shop, said you'd come back to the fold someday.

02:02:36.457 --> 02:02:38.768
- What is it?
- It's called a Zune.

02:02:38.768 --> 02:02:41.056
It's what everybody's listening
to on Earth nowadays.

02:02:41.056 --> 02:02:44.736
- It's got 300 songs on it.
- 300 songs?

02:02:49.996 --> 02:02:51.351
Wait.

02:02:57.697 --> 02:02:59.683
Rocket grabbed the
pieces and re-assembled it.

02:02:59.683 --> 02:03:02.184
But I think Yondu would
want you to have it.

02:03:05.705 --> 02:03:07.005
Thanks.

02:03:08.951 --> 02:03:10.251
Cap'n.

02:03:34.021 --> 02:03:36.796
<i>Father And Son:
Cat Stevens</i>

02:04:24.681 --> 02:04:26.181
They came.

02:04:34.129 --> 02:04:35.429
What is it?

02:04:36.307 --> 02:04:39.027
I sent word to Yondu's
old Ravager buddies.

02:04:39.027 --> 02:04:40.627
And told them what he did.

02:04:44.314 --> 02:04:46.414
It's a Ravager funeral.

02:05:14.884 --> 02:05:17.330
He didn't let us down after all, Captain.

02:05:17.330 --> 02:05:19.355
No he did not, son.

02:05:20.628 --> 02:05:22.628
He did not.

02:05:29.222 --> 02:05:32.110
Fare thee well, old friend.

02:05:35.107 --> 02:05:39.401
Yondu Udonta, I will
see you in the stars.

02:05:43.883 --> 02:05:47.089
- He didn't chase them away.
- No.

02:05:48.278 --> 02:05:50.250
Even though he yelled at 'em.

02:05:50.952 --> 02:05:52.807
And was always mean.

02:05:54.863 --> 02:05:57.310
And he stole batteries
he didn't need.

02:06:02.673 --> 02:06:04.404
Well of course not.

02:06:29.403 --> 02:06:30.703
What?

02:06:31.351 --> 02:06:32.851
It's just...

02:06:35.317 --> 02:06:37.088
...some unspoken thing.

02:06:47.263 --> 02:06:49.123
It's beautiful.

02:06:51.242 --> 02:06:52.542
Yes.

02:06:53.793 --> 02:06:55.309
And so are you.

02:06:58.047 --> 02:06:59.404
On the inside.

02:07:29.062 --> 02:07:33.411
<i>THE GUARDIANS OF THE GALAXY
WILL RETURN.</i>
